column6: Deodorant Stones of America: Thai Crystal Deodorant, 4.25 oz (Pack of 2)
column13: I stopped using deodorant 5 years ago
column14:
It's been about 5 years since I've used regular deodorant. My main concerns about deodorants are parabens, aluminum, and strong fragrances.

I replaced deodorant with a crystal deodorant which works for me. It's easy to use and goes on clear. Simply wet the crystal under running water for just a tad and roll it under armpit.

Pros:
No fragrance.
Goes on clear.
Really does control odor.
Does not contain parabens or aluminum.
Does not stain clothes.

Cons:
If you have a tendency to perspire heavily, this product won't work for you.
If you have a tendency towards developing strong body odors this product may not work for you.
If you drop the crystal it will separate from the base and you will struggle to use it.
This particular size stick doesn't travel well. I need to find a smaller one for my travels.

Will I use this product again? Yes this will continue to be my product of choice.

Who should use this product? This product works for people who do not perspire heavily and who are seeking alternatives to deodorant.

I like it comes in two strengths. I do not see much difference between this one and the 100 strength for the face but that does not mention it is COOL Misting. I use all three pretty much the same. (Try almost any good lip balm with sunscreen at 30-50 and apply to the eye area including yes...right on over the eye lids and all around and OMG you can protect your eyes/skin that is...without pain. I've been applying sunscreen to my eyes for over 30 years now this way when a lip balm came out by Aloe years ago. This is no longer made for about a decade I believe. But I tracked them down even when they moved from Florida up the coast but no longer need to....I do advise finding lip balms unscented no fruity smells etc let alone no taste. It's for your eyes.) Back to these...over all I find this one lasts over a decent amount of time...biking/hiking/even winter sports and apply 2 rarely more than 4 times for a full day in the sun. However..if in and out of water or rain even you may find you need to apply a lot more. It seems to last pretty good..it is not hot...cooling however is subjective to user. I do not find it is a cooling mist. Thus one star down. But it is a good adequate sun screen and also easy to share a spray can with others...like it much better than any lotion out there. PS if you do not have help to put on back or hard to reach areas....the spray can....does allow you to spritz those areas though not as nicely done as if you could spread it on with hands...which I still prefer to do..spray into palm and then spread onto skin to protect. column6: Aztec Secret Indian Healing Clay Deep Pore Cleansing
column13: Use As Mark and To Treat Problem Areas
column14:
This is one product that I keep in my medicine cabinet ALWAYS! I mainly use it to fight acne in 2 different ways.

1. I create a face mask that I rinse off later on while bathing in the tub. I use a small ceramic bowl, add about a tablespoon of the powder and slowly add small amounts of water while stirring. This will prevent the clay from clunking up. I prefer a thicker mask so I add just enough water to create the mask. Then I place it all over my face and neck. If I have extra I place it on my upper chest. You will immediately begin to feel tingling. Your face will then begin to tighten as the clay mask begins to dry. You may even feel your face pulsating. I draw a bath in the meantime. Once I am done with my bath or when the tightness is too much for me, I remove the mask with a washcloth. Simply wet the washcloth with water and pat on the mask to moisten. Then go over again in circular motions until mask is removed. You will have to give your bath an extra rinse since the clay may stick to the tub.

2. I also use the clay for problem areas. Since I too tend to have cystic acne, I immediately mix a small amount of the clay/water and place on the problem area. The clay will reduce the inflammation caused by acne. Sometimes I leave on overnight. I have seen other people suggest mixing the clay with apple cider vinegar so as to prevent harming the skin. So far I have not had any problems. Will try the ACV.

This product is affordable and less expensive than all the other acne treatment products I've purchased in the past.

column6: Best Cellulite Cream with Caffeine and Retinol - For Body, Arms, Legs Firming and Slimming - Strongest Anti Cellulite Treatment can use with massager, wraps, pants and roller gel | MADE IN USA
column14:
How do you compare the hundreds of skin care products? As a regular tester, I've arrived at a list of key considerations. I hope these are helpful to you!
~ Fragrance: Lotiony. None added.
~ Feel during application: Smooth, like a light moisture lotion. Cream is light yellow.
~ Feel after absorption: Smooth, almost powdery, moisturized, no unpleasant film.
~ Is it best for a certain skin type?: Probably okay for all.
~ Is it tested on animals?: No.
~ Packaging: 4oz plastic wide mouth jar with screw on lid.
~ Immediate cosmetic effects:* It leaves skin nice and soft.
~ Potential long-term effectiveness:* Iâ€™m not sold on the idea that a skin cream can treat subdermal fat. But you can make skin tighter and firmer and better conditioned so as to hide the cellulite. This cream might help do that with its retinol and caffeine, and itâ€™s got enough stuff thatâ€™s nice for the skin like shea butter, allantoin, aloe and oils that itâ€™d be worth using even if it didnâ€™t help your cellulite.

*Know the difference between cosmetic and long-term effects: Cosmetic effects are immediate and only present when the product has been applied recently - just like makeup. Long-term effects take longer to see and should remain when you stop using the product (but don't when you find something effective - your skin needs continuing support). The ideal product would be both cosmetically and long-term effective, but it's more realistic to expect a formula to tilt towards one or the other.

I received this free or virtually so for product testing and review. I am under no obligation to provide a positive review and receive no incentives or rewards for doing so. My aim is to highlight features and drawbacks that I would want to know about as a buyer, not hype the product for the manufacturer. My remarks are sincere and my own.

column6: Panasonic Razor, ES-LF51-A, Menâ€™s Electric 4-Blade Cordless Shaver, Wet/Dry with Flexible Pivoting Head
column14:
I had been using a Phillips Norelco Arcitec shaver since 2008. The Arcitec shaver still works, still takes a charge and still provides a pretty good shave. However, the blades are getting a bit dull and the Arcitec itself was getting close to 8 years old.

While looking for a new shaving head, I found that the design had been changed and that many people were not happy with the change. Shave heads with the original design were selling for almost $200.

I decided rather than to buy a new and maybe not so good replacement head for the 8 year old Arcitec that I would look for a different shaver.

I found the Panasonic ES-LF51-A Arc 4 wet or dry electric shaver. The reviews were mostly good and the total cost was about twice that of new design replacement heads for my Phillips Arcitec shaver. So, new shaver, new shaving head at a relatively low cost â€“ did not seem too bad so I ordered one from Amazon.

First impressions were that it had a good solid feel and finish. The rubberized portions of the shaver body provide for a solid grip and were a nice addition.

The shaving head can be locked into position or can be set to articulate as you shave.

I plugged it in to charge the battery before I started it. Charging took about an hour. The shaver has LEDâ€™s that indicate the level of charge.

On starting the shaver, I noticed that it operated with a high frequency buzz. This was not a surprise since the description from the manufacturer says that it operates at 14,000 RPM.

The high frequency buzz is especially noticeable when the shaver is close to the ear. Fortunately, time spent with the shaver close to the ear is minimal in most cases so the noise is not a big problem.

I tried it on my beard but could not do a good test since I had shaved that morning with a blade. I decided to allow my beard to grow for a couple of days so that I could do a fair test.

A couple dayslater, I tried the shaver again. The first thing I noticed was that the Panasonic seems to be a â€œlinearâ€ shaver. By â€œlinearâ€ I mean that I found that I was more or less required to shave using parallel strokes. I had been shaving with a rotary shaver for the past eight years so became accustomed to using a circular shaving pattern. When I tried using a circular shaving pattern with the Panasonic, it just did not feel right.

I know that Panasonic says that one should use the shaver for 30 days before making a judgment but it seemed that the parallel shaving pattern caused me to miss places. I changed the direction of the parallel strokes to be sure to catch all of my beard. I used the shaver for two weeks before making the decision to return it

The quality of the shave is good. There were only a few places (as with the Arcitec) where I had to repeatedly make passes to remove the stubble.

Instructions say to apply liquid soap to the shaver head and enter cleaning mode on the shaver to clean it. To enter cleaning mode, hold the power button in for a couple of seconds. The shaver goes into really high frequency operation on a timer. Once cleaning mode has finished, the shaver turns off. The heads can then be rinsed with cold water and you are ready to go again.

The Panasonic is a wet or dry shaver but I never used it as a wet shaver. I think that as long as I am going to put shaving cream on my face, I might as well use a blade. A fresh blade provides a better shave than any electric shaver I have ever used.

I guess that I could have tried the Panasonic while in the shower but then I would need a mirror.

Shaving without a mirror is OK for a â€œrough inâ€ shave that might be adequate for weekends but if one is going to work or on a date then a mirror is required to be sure that sideburns are trimmed neatly and that no paces have been missed.

Having a mirror in the shower is problematicbecause it gets steamed up or wet so that details are hard to see. Besides, how much time can one afford to spend in the shower?

I did not use the trimmer on the Panasonic and I do not use the trimmer on my Arcitec.

I figure that I have to go into the bathroom eventually so while there, I trim sideburns with a blade â€“ much more accurate. Using a blade allows for a â€œsurgicalâ€ trim because the blade does not obstruct my view of where I want to trim and it is light in weight and easier â€“ in my opinion â€“ to manipulate than a shaver.

If you ever go to a â€œrealâ€ old time barber, they will trim your sideburns, neck and hairline with a straight razor and not clippers. Having a razor sharp blade in the hands of a relative stranger so close to your carotid artery provides for a bit of apprehension but it adds to the over all barber experience.

I am retired now but when I worked each day, I used the electric shaver as part of morning preparation multitasking. With an electric shaver, I could shave while checking the news, weather or traffic on TV and while having morning coffee.

Additionally, with a shaver that allows a circular shaving pattern, shaving can be a more or less absent minded procedure that is not available if I need to pay attention to the direction of parallel shaving strokes and checking for missed spots.

As a final test before I decided to return the Panasonic, I shaved and then took notice of the quality of the shave with the Panasonic. I waited a couple of days for my beard to grow again and then shaved with the 8 year old Arcitec with the year old shaving head and again took notice of the quality of the shave.

The comparison of shave quality between the Panasonic and Arcitec did not show enough difference in to warrant keeping the Panasonic shaver with its parallel shaving requirement.

Bottom line: The Panasonic shaver provides a very close shave. However,the fact that it is in my opinion a parallel device causes it not to be acceptable for my purposes.

column6: Revitalash Advanced Eyelash Conditioner, 3.5 ml/0.118 Fl Oz
column14: I've never been blessed in the eyelash department. It takes a lot of work to plump and lengthen my lashes. No matter what mascara or expensive eyelash curler I bought--the results were so-so. I have pulled my lashes out accidentally on a few occasions, leaving sparse patches on my lid. Instead of going for eyelashes extension, I decided to invest and experiment with a treatment, and debated between Revitalash and Latisse. Both had great reviews, and although Latisse seems to have a stronger formula--the perk of not needing a prescription led me to try Revitalash first. Most reviews said they saw results in 3 months. I have to say: I noticed big results in just two! My sparse spots filled in and my lashes are longer and stronger. It's nothing I so much noticed with bare lashes, but once I put mascara on--there was a world of difference from before. Can't wait to see the full results in another 4 months. Highly recommend. Word of advice: be patient, use every night, and be realistic with your expectations.

column6: HotroseÂ® US Cosmetic Makeup Brush Finger Glove Silicone Hand Cleaning Tools (Light Green)
column13: Winner silicone washboard compared to the others
column14:
Very happy with this product. I'm posting this review on the day I received the product which was the 1st day of the estimated delivery time period. I attached this product to an order with other products so that i can use the free shipping service from amazon (for elligible orders above 35$) and it actually arrived first before anything else.
1. This little product is like a silicon washboard for make-up brushes and sponges. I generally use warm to hot water and soft soap to clean off my brushes so as to kill germs and remove leftovers from makeup products. The material of the silicon finger glove is thick enough yet still flexible so that it wasn't affected at all after I tested for the first time by letting hot water run over it for several minutes. Major plus, since i didn't want to end up with a product going gummy soft under high temperature due to thin structure.
2. The size of this product allowed me to hold it by one finger (there's not much room for two unless you have really small fingers) when cleaning my brushes, while supporting it with the rest of my fingers. But I could also skip that and just hold it in my palm. Overall, it's medium size, easy, has the shape of half an egg and quite comfortable to use.
3. I used the ridges of the product for cleaning make-up brushes and sponges while running them softly perpendicular to the ridges, and the little dots at the end for eye-shadow brushes. Honestly, the shape offers quite some flexibility with what you want to clean depending on the size of the brush. I liked though that it has those little dots at the end, since they helped me clean thoroughly smaller brushes and make sure that the hairs were free of product. Also, the dots/ridges of the silicon glove helps building a lather with soap a lot easier, and like any washboard don't expect it to clean your brushes for you, it only serves as a very nifty surface while you do the work.
4. Most importantly, at least for me, I noticed the price. I compared it to other similar products of the same material, shape and function and the one by Hotrose pulls ahead. It's only 4.99 $ (currently, at the time of the review) compared to more expensive ones, and as I mentioned in the beginning I ordered it among other products and chose the free shipping service from amazon.com, since this little product is actually elligible for the free shipping service from amazon.com when other similar ones are not, adding quite the cost on such a small simple cleaning product. It arrived fast, in perfect condition and didn't have to pay shipping fees. Overall, very satisfied with seller, price and quality.ce. column13: It's Got Potential, Exept I Bought The Wrong (Too Light) Shade...
column14:
I could really like this product, except I should probably have gotten a darker shade. I bought this for the first time a couple of weeks ago (at a local drug store) because I'm having trouble with dark circles under my eyes and haven't really found anything that solves that problem in a way that I'm totally satisfied with yet. This is the best thing I've tried so far. Contrary to some of the other reviewers, I found that the different colors were not at all just on the surface but (so far) seem to completely permeate the compact. There doesn't seem to be a whole lot of pigment to the green & pink, but I am tempted to chalk that up to the fact that this one is simply too light for me, and if I don't find that this issue as well as the one of generally too-faint coverage (which makes occasional touch-ups an absolute necessity) are resolved by buying a deeper shade of this product, I will include that & any other pertinent info in an update.

I am using this product even though it is much too light for me, it does seem to blend pretty well with another powder I have that is somewhat too dark and has a tendency to look too "heavy." So, in my case, two of my makeup purchasing mistakes seem to be cancelling each other out with pretty good results LOL ;)

I absolutely do plan on purchasing this product again, only in the next darker shade.I am very fair and I normally purchase either the very lightest, or next to the very lightest shade of powders and concealers. However, from what I can see, this product is probably going to be pretty much useless for anyone but those ladies who are very, very advanced in beauty (as only ladies over about 70 or so years old have been able to achieve.) I tried it on a friend of mine who, if nekkid, could lean up against a freshly painted eggshell whilte wall and blend right in if she wasn't also a flaming ginger. Amazinly, this stuff was a bit too light for her as well.
Then, I tried it on my gorgeous 83 year old neighbor and viola! Perfection! It looked so good on her I thought I might not get it back from her, good thing she is a drinker and somewhat forgetful hahaha!

No one who has not had at least 70 years on this earth in which to become an expert level genius in beauty is lovely and fair enough to wear the lightest shade of this product, so even if you are Irish or just extremely pasty for some other reason, you still really need to get a darker shade if you don't want to appear even more ghoulish than you already do all by yourself. Also, I have noticed that this product seems to look and cover best when applied with a large powder or "kabuki" brush (how appropriate, amirite?) than it does when applied with the dumb little flat brush that comes with it or a powder puff. For precision appplication and coverage, such as under the eyes, use a medium-soft or a medium bristle eyeshadow brush (a really soft brush just gets it everywhere but where you want it and is an exercise in frustration more than anything else.)ear old neighbor and viola! Perfection! It looked so good on her I thought I might not get it back from her, good thing she is a drinker and somewhat forgetful hahaha!

column13: Another awesome carrier oil for your essential oil collection!
column14:
As an avid user of essential oils, I'm always on the lookout for new oils/carrier oils so I can mix up new concoctions. I don't ever use carrier oils in the diffuser, but I do use them to mix up face washes, hair conditioners, moisturizers, etc.

I've been using this oil mixed with jojoba for hair conditioner and I gotta say it has made my hair look super healthy and has made it very soft. I've also heard its very good for skin aliments so the next time I get an acne breakout I will definitely be giving it a try.

Overall, this seems like a really great carrier oil. My go to is usually coconut oil but I actually like this better because it has almost no scent and I believe it feels a little less greasy but that might just be me.

Plant Therapy had some overstock of this Evening Primrose oil and agreed to give me a discount if I would test it out and leave a review. Having said that, I take reviews seriously and I'm under no obligation to leave a good review. The opinions above are my own and my honest opinion is that this is a fantastic carrier oil for anyones essential oil collection!

column6: Tom's of Maine Women's Antiperspirant Deodorant Natural Powder - 2.25 Oz, Pack of 3
column13: Definitely control perspiration and has a nice fragrance
column14:
It's been about 5 years since I've used regular deodorant. My main concerns about deodorants are parabens, aluminum, and strong fragrances.

I replaced deodorant with a crystal body deodorant stick which works for me. This summer I decided to use this Tom's of Maine Deodorant because it is also an antiperspirant. This is something my crystal stick doesn't offer. I solely intend to use it for hot days when I may perspire the most.

Pros:
It does control my perspiration which is what I wanted.
The natural powder fragrance is nice since more fragrances annoy me.

Cons:
Will stain dark clothes with a white residue like most deodorants.
One has to scrub harder to remove the deodorant from the armpit.

Will I use this product again? Yes but only during the hottest months of the year. I plan on returning to my crystal deodorant that still keeps odors away. I don't mind light perspiration since I think it's healthy for the body. I'm glad I tried this product. It's an option.

Who should use this product? Well it depends on your needs and issues with deodorants.

column13: This morning I already noticed that the crepiness under my eyes has slightly improved which is WONDERFUL. All my other wrinkles
column14: I just received my peel last night and used it straight away. I was a tiny bit nervous since this is my first peel ever. I followed the directions with cleansing and using the alcohol to prep. And then I applied the glycolic with a cotton ball. It stung but really hardly at all. I was able to leave it on for a full 3 minutes and could have gone longer but didn't want to push it for my first time. I rinsed with the baking soda/water solution and then warm water. My skin only got a little red and that quickly dissipated. Right away it felt extra smooth and soft. I slathered my face with coconut oil after. This morning I already noticed that the crepiness under my eyes has slightly improved which is WONDERFUL. All my other wrinkles look the same so far - I'm 51 so there's a lot. But I think if I continue this every week I will see other improvements.

column6: 2 Pack L'Oreal Paris Hair Color Superior Preference Mousse Absolue, 1000 Pure Lightest Blonde
column14:
I am completely satisfied with this stuff. I recently dyed my light brown hair a darkish platinum blonde, and I just did not want to spend so much money at the salon to touch up my roots. I liked the concept of this product, so I purchased it on a whim. I got a little worried when I read all the awful reviews about it, but I had a very satisfying experience. This was my first time ever using a home hair dye, and I was delightfully surprised.
While my roots are still visible, the dye DEFINITELY made them lighter and they blend better with the rest of my hair. I think the key to this stuff is really massaging it into your head. The pictures in the directions don't really show that, but it does say it in the directions. Not only did it lighten up my roots, it also helped to tone down the yellowness that comes with bleached hair. I also added some toning conditioner (the John Frieda purple one) to it, and that made it look really shiny and platinum. A lot of reviews were complaining about the smell, but if you've ever had your hair dyed or bleached, you should be fine. Finally, I had my mom actually apply it (her first time with a home hair dye too!) and I honestly think it would be so hard to do it by yourself. So, my advice would be to ask someone to help. Overall, great product!

Helping smaller businesses who make quality products is a rewarding thing to do...

column6: Waterpik Waterpik Ultra Dental Water Jet Flosser Wp-100
column14:
I am an adult with braces, 35yr, just had them 'installed' a few months ago. I do not know why in the world orthodontists don't automatically send you home with one of these after your new 'hardware' has been mounted in place! I now realize that my teeth have never actually been clean this whole time and that includes 15-20 minutes a night with special brushes, impossible floss and other 'tools' for these braces.

My parents had an old Waterpik (same model, old packaging) that kept on working, so I borrowed it for a few nights and didn't want to part. It was beautifully gross to see all the 'extra' food flush out of my mouth with the waterpik and that was AFTER brushing and brushing and re-brushing to get them clean. I never realized how much was actually left in there, hidden from the brush, stuck under the metal, bacteria waiting to feed off it.

Please, for the love of your teeth, if you have braces, order a waterpik! You are already purchasing a 'major appliance' for your mouth anyway, just think of this as insurance for it. A small investment to pay for a happier smile. And toss the nasty and pointless toothpaste... just use baking soda on your brush and/or dissolve some in the water to use in the waterpik. Baking soda helps to balance the pH levels in your mouth so bad bacteria can't grow... Like you can even pronounce the ingredients in your tube of paste, let alone know what its really doing to your mouth!

By the way, my three children, 5, 8, 12, love it also! I wouldn't get the 'Kid' version if your little ones are 6-7 or older as my 8yr is already at level 6 in the intensity and the kid version only goes up to 3. I guess level 3 is fine for some people, but I am using this in place of floss because of braces and you need more intensity then 3 to get the job done. And since these last a long time, your kids will probably grow out of the level 3 quickly. Just a thought.

So, if you want a clean mouth, braces or not, toss some baking soda in the water tub with warm water, stir and cut on the dentist in a tube. Slowly work your way up to 9 or 10 (over a few weeks) and get ready to feel satisfied! â˜ºr not, toss some baking soda in the water tub with warm water, stir and cut on the dentist in a tube. Slowly work your way up to 9 or 10 (over a few weeks) and get ready to feel satisfied! â˜º

column6: Waterpik Classic Professional Water Flosser (WP-72)
column13: No nozzles in box; not as good as current models
column14: Bought this on sale ($34) to be a backup in case my more current waterpik stopped working.  That day came yesterday.  Broke through the manufacturer's seal and pulled out the contents only to discovery that no nozzles were included.  Because I bought it a year ago, it's too late to return to Amazon.  Tried to use the nozzles from my other waterpiks, but none of them work.  Need the ones especially made for this model.  So now I have to buy these hard-to-find replacement nozzles that aren't sold by Waterpik, and also, aren't cheap. Even if they are the right ones for this model, not sure they would work well.  Without the nozzles in place, the water pressure seems to be weak.  The unit also has a clumsier setup than the newer models. A much larger water tank rests on top of the entire unit.  When it's in pace and full of water, I'm thinking about whether it's stable.  Stable or not, it's harder to get to the buttons and nozzle thing.  All things considered, wish I had never bought this. Going to cut my losses, throw it away, and get a newer model. Hard to understand why another company isn't making a good-quality alternative and giving Waterpik some competition.

column14: I am seriously in love with these La Lune charcoal konjac sponges. I used a different brand for a plain konjac sponge around a year ago and it was okay, nothing to write home about, I even forgot about it and stopped using it. The texture is soothing, there arent any odd smells, and having a rounded and a flat side make it super easy to adjust to the contours of your face. I havent used them with soap, just warm water, but my facial skin looks good. I am pregnant, and not the pretty glowy skin kind either. My face has been dull and uneven no matter what I do. Within 2 or 3 days of using the La Lune charcoal sponge I noticed I was less dull and more even. To be fair, I am also approaching the third trimester, so hormones could be playing their role, but I credit the sponge. I buff my face in circular motions with it for about 2 or so minutes. (So long largely just because it feels so nice!) I do have pretty sensitive skin, but I have not reacted poorly at all and I have been using it for roughly 2 weeks. So see, it doesnt take long to fall in love with them! I am giving these to all the women on my holiday gift list this year, that is how strongly I endorse this product. I look forward to trying other La Lune products since this one is so wonderful.

column6: BTArtbox 100% All Natural Facial Cleansing & Exfoliating Beauty Sponges Lavender Konjac Sponge
column14:
I've been using Konjac sponges for quite a while now and love how gently they clean and exfoliate my skin, and I haven't had any issues with blackheads or acne since using them. This Konjac sponge is a shriveled hard rock when it arrives, but don't let that fool you because if you'll soak it in a bowl of lukewarm water for a few minutes the sponge nearly doubles in size and becomes soft and cushiony. You can then use the sponge as it is or in conjunction with your regular facial cleanser remove makeup, dirt, and oil. I like to use mine along with my Vitamin C facial cleanser when I shower, and I use the Konjac to gently massage my face in circular motions for about 30 seconds.

These sponges let you get right up into your pores for a deep clean that clears away dead skin cells, clogged pores, and oils. The unique net-like structure of the sponge gently massages and revitalizes my complexion leaving my face feeling soft and renewed. Squeeze the Konjac sponge between your palms to wring out the water when you're finished using it, then let it air dry in a well ventilated place using the attached cotton string. Get your sponge wet and soft again before each use and it should last for several months. I didn't particularly care for the scent of this sponge, but I love how soothing and gentle it feels when I use it. Retail sample provided at no cost for evaluation and review purposes. My review is based entirely on my own opinions formed by using the Lavender Konjac Sponge in order to evaluate and test it.

column6: Crest 3D White Brilliance Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Deep Cleansing via Daily Two-Step System, 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
column14: I've been using the Crest 3D White Daily Cleansing and Whitening System for the past two weeks since I received it from BzzAgent and Crest for free to try and provide feedback. I am reviewing based on my initial reactions and will update my review after continued use. The system is comprised of two products. Step 1 is for for deep cleaning and Step 2 is a polishing/whitening agent. You use each step for one minute; spit after Step 1 but do not rinse. Step 1 seemed like regular toothpaste and had a similar "taste." It did not seem to get very bubbly. I prefer a toothpaste with more "suds" because I feel like I get a better clean. With that said, however, I do feel like my teeth are cleaner than with my previous toothpaste. I also was not a fan of the "not rinsing" aspect before brushing with step 2. Gross. Step 2 didn't taste great but was much better than the traditional strips. You could faintly smell/taste the hydrogen peroxide but it was ok. The second time I used the product I could feel a slight tingling but no sensitivity which was nice. I did "feel" like it was working. Pros so far: motivates me to brush for a full 2 minutes and twice a day, not bad tasting, gentle whitening, not messy, not an extra product or time spent (just usual teeth brushing which you should be doing anyway. Cons: toothpaste doesn't get bubbly, whitening effects are gradual and not immediate, not supposed to rinse in between steps.

column6: Sally Hansen Hard As Nails Clear
column13: Seriously, the only product that really works for split nails is Gorilla Glue
column14:
Don't waste your money on this product. It doesn't harden your nails and glossy nail polish is probably cheaper. If you are bothered by splitting nails, the ONLY product I've found that really works is Gorilla Glue. Here's how you should apply it:

Squirt a drop of Gorilla Glue onto a piece of wax paper--don't squirt it directly onto your split nail, or you will end up gluing your nail to your finger.

Take a toothpick and apply the gorilla glue to the split in your nail.

After the glue has dried, cut your nail short, leaving as little of the split as you possibly can. The remaining split with its spot of glue will grow out in due time and you can trim it off.

column6: Grisi Sulfur Soap with Lanolin for Acne - 2 Pack
column14:
I have had great skin almost my whole life. Even throughout puberty my skin was pretty decent. No acne, just occasional breakouts. But a few months ago I got these awful little bumps on my temples. They weren't zits and had nothing in them. They were skin colored and just felt like sandpaper. And you could only see them if the light hit my face right. So I didn't think too much about it and figured they'd go away on their own eventually if I left them alone. But nope. They spread down my jawline and onto my cheeks. So the entire lower portion of my face was like a giant swath of sandpaper. Ugh! Then in a matter of days it turned into deep cystic acne. I had a friend look at me one day and think I had fallen off a bike or something because it looked like my cheek was gouged because it was so red and swollen. I have been trying EVERYTHING to get rid of it. First I went makeup free, took recommended supplements, exercised, drank lots of water, ate healthier than I already do. And definitely didn't touch it. But none of that helped so I started looking into different products. I've been using this sulfur soap for a few months now. And, I don't think my acne is the kind that is responding to it very much. I did notice that it has helped keep it in check because I forgot it on vacation for a few days and my skin did not like that. But it also hasn't healed it. Still searching for the holy grail that will solve whatever it is that's molesting my face. But until then this is helping me at least keep it from getting worse.

UPDATE: After trying this for a while I had to give it up and went a dermatologist. Now, finally, my acne is cleared up. I began using benzoyl peroxide wash during the time I was still recovering from it. But after it was cleared I tried using this again. I figured sulfur soap would be much less harsh. Nope. My skin broke out immediately. I figured maybe it was just a coincidence and tried it again at a later time. Same thing. I wanted it to work so I tried it again later on. Still a no go. Each time I used this my skin broke out. I gave it a few more goes. But after trying it multiple times I finally had to admit it couldn't be caused by anything else. It was the soap. I'm pretty sad because I much prefer the idea of using sulfur on my skin to other harsher alternatives. However, I did find a sulfur scrub that my skin loves ([...]). So that isn't to say you should rule out sulfur. You just have to find the product that fits you just right. And for me this wasn't it.ried it again later on. Still a no go. Each time I used this my skin broke out. I gave it a few more goes. But after trying it multiple times I finally had to admit it couldn't be caused by anything else. It was the soap. I'm pretty sad because I much prefer the idea of using sulfur on my skin to other harsher alternatives. However, I did find a sulfur scrub that my skin loves ([...]). So that isn't to say you should rule out sulfur. You just have to find the product that fits you just right. And for me this wasn't it.

column6: OZ Naturals - The BEST Natural Sunscreen For Anti Aging - SPF 30 Mineral Sunscreen - This Broad Spectrum, Zinc Oxide Sunscreen Is Safe For All Skin Types & Reduces the Risk of Early Skin Aging Caused By the Sun
column13: Solid protection but piles for me.
column14:
First things first, this is vegan and cruelty free which is awesome. My favorite thing about this product is its actives. Titanium Dioxide and Zinc Oxide are physical blockers which means they are not absorbed into the blood stream but also means the product will protect you longer. These sit on the surface of skin reflecting light rather than chemical sunscreens that work through the layers of skin. Chemical sunscreens absorb sun light.

This sunscreen is white cast and of a heavier weight you'd expect with sunscreen. The photos are of my legs. It does have a white cast as you can see but that's almost guaranteed with 6% zinc oxide. My biggest qualm with this sunscreen, and why I removed a star, is that it piles. I tried patting it on, rubbing, and nothing stopped it from clotting up. On my legs though, it's hardly noticeable.

That said, you could try putting on a moisturizer before hand to create a less dry environment than my legs appear to be?

HINT: If you look closely, my knees look like Ninja Turtles

column6: Dove Men+Care Antiperspirant & Deodorant, Fresh Awake 2.7 Ounces
column14:
PROS:
* It stops the sweat

CONS:
* Irritates my skin.

As a kid, I had to be careful of what soaps I used, or I would break out. From adolescence on (I'm almost 40 now), I've not had any problems with skin irritation from anything, whether it's deodorants, laundry soap, garage chemicals, whatever.

Except this. I bought 5 different deodorants to try out, and this is the only one that makes my pits itchy. I'm fine for most of the day, but then in the afternoon, and for several days after, I'm itchy.

I would call this 1 star, but this stops the sweat. Many deodorants/antiperspirants just don't work very well, but this one does.

The problem chemical is C12-15 Alkyl Benzoate. That's the one missing from Degree Adrenaline, which works just as well, but without skin itchies. The strong, active ingredient is Aluminum Zirconium Tetrachlorohydrex. Anything 15-20% of AZT works well for me.

column6: Neutrogena MoistureShine Lip Soother, SPF 20
column13: This is my favorite favorite favorite SPF Lip Gloss
column14:
I do spoil myself with lipgloss. It's completely out of character, but I trend toward super chapped lips, and lipgloss is as easy to put on as chapstick. Some lipglosses, like this one, outlast chapstick by a LOT. Ok, here's the rundown.

Color: Sheer, shiny, and subtle. I like that! Some people don't, and prefer more pigment.
SPF: 20. And it works. My lips burn, so I feel like a good judge of these things.
Feel: Wet & smooth. I really like the feel, and would compare it to Buxom, though of course it doesn't tingle and it fortunately it isn't nearly as sticky. In fact, I'd call it slippery. My SO still dubs me "Princess Sticky-Lips" when it's on, though, so apparently it doesn't feel as nice to smooch.
Durability: Magic. :) I really like that part! It easily lasts as long as Buxom, if not longer, and it outlasts Soft Lips and the fruity Blistex chapsticks, my other two go-to SPF lip products, by leaps and bounds.
Flavor & Smell: pleasant and fruity. Slightly more sophisticated than fruit punch, but that's the closest smell I can think of.

So, I'm a fan. I hope this review helps you determine whether you would be, too!

column13: Helps keep my skin clear and glowing
column14:
I have oily, acne-prone skin. I have dealt with acne for almost 30 years so I have to be very cautious about what skincare products I use. I was successfully using a prescription topical medication with a retinoid that is no longer covered by my insurance. It is expensive to buy on its own. Therefore I needed to revamp my skin care routine to stay blemish free without it. I needed affordable products that work. I also purchased a sonic face brush to help with exfoliation. Currently I use a cleanser, two serums, a product with benozoyl peroxide and then a moisturizer each evening (all products but the one with benzoyl peroxide are from InstaNatural).

I prefer skincare products that are vegan and not tested on animals because I have been a vegetarian for 22 years. I have been using InstaNatural Retinol Moisturizer once a day in the pm for about 3 weeks.You just need a pump for the face and neck. It absorbs quickly. In conjunction with the InstaNatural serums and other products, it helps keep my skin clear and glowing. I would recommend this product. Please wear sunscreen every day because retinol and retinoid products make your skin more prone to sun damage.

column13: I wanted to love it, and give it a chance
column14: I just tried the 2-way Instyler (Purple, 1.25") after using the Original for years. It took me 2+ hours to do my hair (longish) as opposed to 45-60 mins with the Original - I do have thick, wavy/unmanageable hair, but that's not an excuse for why it took so long. Its highest heat setting definitely does not get as hot as the Original - strange, because it's supposed to go up to 425 F vs 410 F on the Original. And don't get me started on the 2-way feature - it was supposed to make my life easier, but I think the reason it took me so long to do my hair was because the barrel changed directions on me so many times, and this, without my consciously double-tapping it. I admit it's a bit of a learning curve, but my hair also did get caught on the edge of the barrel several times, and I lost more than a few strips of hair to entanglement - even had to snip off some hair with a pair of scissors :-( This NEVER happened to me with the Original. The bristles on this are flimsier too than on the Original... Overall, I wanted to love it, and give it a chance, but it's back to the Original for me. It really worked wonders on my thick, unmanageable long hair.

column13: I like to blow dry my hair especially in the winter
column14: I like to blow dry my hair especially in the winter.  However when I blow dry it becomes frizzy which drives me nuts.  I had heard about argan oil from a friend so when I was offered the chance to review this Elbahya Argan Oil I jumped on the chance.  I did get this at a reduced price but it worked so well I would pay full price for it.  I decided to try this on my hair first.  I started out with about three drops and worked it into my ends.  I also worked some more towards the top of my hair and scalp, this is where I end up having flyaways.  I blow dried as normal and was so happy to see that the oil not only tamed my frizz, but it also made my hair softer.  I also had good results when using it on my face.  It absorbs quickly and leaves your face feeling soft.  It's a great product for the money and because you use very little each time, it lasts for a while.

column6: For Pro Ultrasonic Diffuser, Namaste
column14:
NAMASTE -- (Hindi) Traditional Indian greeting, with both palms together, thumbs over the heart. Then, a slight bow is performed.

Of course, you don't need to practice Yoga, or listen to Sitar music, in order to appreciate the beauty of this well designed diffuser, with its relaxing light show, and cool mist diffusing various essential oils. I think the design of this diffuser is well done. Even though its faux wood, you really have to look twice, before you believe its not real. In the base of the diffuser are the function buttons. One button activates the mist function, with two choices for mist intensity, light or heavy. The other button controls the mood lighting, that illuminates the white sleeve that covers the water tank. Every diffuser I've ever seen or reviewed, has something about it that makes it unique. This diffuser has a mood lighting, that differs from all other diffusers. Normally the colors slowly morph into each other. So the Blue turns turquois, then to forest green, then a light spring green, into yellow, orange, etc. Not this diffuser. You turn it on, and you get dark blue. Then, it flashes into light blue. Then its suddenly green, then indigo, then red. Of course, you can just pick a color, and let the diffuser remain lit on that color. The water tank holds 120ml, about half a cup, but I added a bit more water, and didn't notice any problems with the mist quality or quantity. Add a few drops of your essential oil into the water, no more than 5 or 6 drops are needed. Then, relax. When it runs out of water, the STOP light flashes. (Right below the MIST and LIGHT indicator lights, between the buttons.) Never put "perfume oils", or other cheap fragrance liquids inside the tank. Don't even use essential oils, that have been diluted with Jojoba oil either. Those oils will create a gunk around the diffuser's ceramic disc, that produces the ultrasonic vibration. The great thing about a diffuser, is that you can stop spraying artificial air fresheners, or scented candles, and other artificial odors into your home. Those chemicals go into the air you breathe. Then, they go in the body. Personally, I'm allergic to artificial fragrances. They smell like chemicals, harsh, and often sharp. Instead, imagine the soft, relaxing fragrance of the herb fields of France, covered with Lavender. Or the orange groves of Arabia. Perhaps the myrrh trees in Somalia, or cinnamon oil from Madagascar. A personal favorite is a diffuser filled with Patchouli oil from mystical India, perhaps mixed into Sandalwood oil. If I'm suffering from a lung ailment, with a cough, I use some peppermint and a touch of Eucalyptus. For headaches, the traditional favorite of the Queen of Hungry was Eau de Cologne, which was 2 drops lavender oil, 2 drops orange oil (or bergamot oil is better), and 3 drops of Rosemary oil. Aromatherapy is fine art for the nose. As you practice this art, you'll develop a more keen sense of smell. Plus, if you want to study the lore and history behind various smells, you could by a book on aromatherapy, or the history of perfumery. This is a fascinating subject, very much tied into herbology. Instead of distilling the herbs and drinking the tea, or swallowing the herbs in capsules, the herbs' most important (essential) oils are extracted and bottled. With essential oils and a diffuser, the healing properties of the seeds, leaves, bark, flowers or fruits are drawn into the cool mist, then diffused into the air. As the lung and sinuses inhale the aroma, the healing properties of the essential oils start to work. Some oils will stimulate the body, like Peppermint, some relax, like lavender. Some oils have the properties of incense, creating a soft mood in a room, and masking any animal smell, or lack of bathing. (Its true, even the wealthiest people in the middle ages seldom bathed. Instead, they poured perfume on themselves. Deodorants have been around for a long time.) Good deodorant smells include oil of rose, (yin, very spiritual), or Patchouli oil (yang in quality, you will either love or hate the smell. I love it) even Frankincense or Myrrh. Why not put essential oil of Pine into a diffuser during Christmas, especially if you have an artificial tree? You could buy essential oil of citronella, and use your diffuser outside, during a picnic. I have somewhere between 30 to 40 various essential oils, and often mix them into my own, personal creations to compliment or change my mood. Or cover over my cat's smell. However, you dont need to start out with all that. Perhaps buy an essential Oil kit, with 6 different scents, or even just buy two or three essential oils when you purchase this diffuser. I would recommend peppermint (in case you're sick, or want a stimulating smell), then buy Orange oil, Lavender oil, then an essential oil that speaks to you personally, like Cedarwood oil, or Patchouli. Women love Ylang-Ylang oil, which smells very close to Jasmine. Whatever you decide, you know that you are going to help your lungs recover from years of artificial smells from candles, air fresheners and fragrance oils. So much information can be found on line on aromatherapy, however, drop me a line in the comments if you need a bit of info, and I'll do my best to help you.
I was provided a free diffuser in exchange for my fair and honest review.rose, (yin, very spiritual), or Patchouli oil (yang in quality, you will either love or hate the smell. column6: Batiste 6.73 fl oz Dry Shampoo by Batiste Strength and Shine
column13: Makes me not look like an old French whore!
column14:
Thanks to Batiste dry shampoo, I'm able to continue perpetuating the lazy millennial lifestyle that every other generation stereotypes me as, by not washing my hair everyday--or even every other day for that matter! It does an acceptable job of keeping the grease at bay from my already dull-looking hair, preventing me from looking like a homeless person trying to pass as a business professional in an attempt to get free coffee from the company's generic Keurig.

I've used several dry shampoos from the Batiste line and this is their most pleasing scent by far. To me, their "Fresh" scent smells like straight-up-now-tell-me Lysol, "Cherry" smells like cancer and "Blush" smells like a douche, and I'm not talking about the word douche as a euphemism for Donald Trump, I'm talking about a literal cleansing douche. Unless "Strength & Shine" is an odor now, this particular scent is elusively unnamed. It smells somewhat masculine, which I like, but is also oddly feminine. If Tilda Swinton came out with a fragrance, this would be it. Totes.

In conclusion, it's a good dry shampoo, for the price, and doesn't leave behind a lot of white residue. I gave it four stars because they are liar-liars-with-their-pants-on-fire due to fact that it doesn't make/keep my hair shiny. I want my pink shirt back! I also cannot attest to the strength claim; but let's keep it real, what kind of psycho hose beast has the time or resources to test that assertion? Well-executed marketing ploy, Batiste, well-executed.

column14:
I absolutely adore Majestic pure essential oils. The quality is fantastic! I can never wait to open the bottle. My daughter even asks for the bottle lid (we put the dropper in and leave it because we use the oil so often) and keeps the lid in a little box so she can smell it whenever she wants to. I use at least 7 to 8 drops of lavender per day, and 3 or 4 drops on my kids box fan. It really has helped them sleep at night. One of the kiddos used to stay up all night long when she could, which made for a grouch all day. Finally one night when she was still up at 5:30 AM, I came and brought her a few drops of lavender as a "medicine" to put on her pillow and help her sleep. A few sniffs and she settled down to fall asleep. Now she gets the drops on her box fan every night so the whole room smells of lavender. I absolutely cannot do without a big bottle of lavender in the house, and majestic pure never disappoints!

column6: End-Zit Acne Control Drying Lotion
column14:
This is good for blending on into your face as you put on your make up or foundation for hiding blemishes. But didn't work for me. Not for big pimple like I have a very persistent one that like to grow big.
For a background, I always have a one and only zit anywhere on my face almost every month
for as long as I can remember. I thought this one would give me a quick heal of the problem (particularly this month!) like I was hoping. I'm a proactive user as of the moment for say 2-3 yrs now, it doesn't even work for me a hundred percent but I still use it. It does keep my face smoother. But it doesn't get rid of my zit that comes after or before my period. And that is what I'm looking for, something that is not for the entire face but something that would stop or prevent my pimple to become big. I don't have this small
stubborn pimples that others like to get rid of, but my problem is this one that would turn into big zit on my face and last like 8--10 days of giving me an embarrassment when I go out but I really need to to pick up my kids or do errands for example that I just suck it up and ignore the looks from people. Though im so tired of it coz it's embarrassing! But what can I do.
Sorry that this product is not working for me so I'm going to say I just keep on looking.
I don't always give reviews but I want to share my disappointment. Maybe it works for others Quick! But not for all!
This picture was taken last Friday and we went out to pizza dinner with my In laws and this review is today is Friday and it is still big. I didn't want to come but then again I just have to. The third picture shown was taken after a week and you can see it is still big.
I kept on putting the end-zit several times a day and to no avail, I just wait for it to heal on its own. Oh well.

column6: Revlon Frost & Glow Highlighting Kit 1 ea
column13: Would NEVER use another highlighting kit
column14:
If you're a brunette, don't buy any other highlighting kit. (Warning--Loreal has a "Frost and Glow" kit, but it's NOT the same, which I learned the hard way.) This Revlon kit doesn't leave your hair brassy, just nice and golden. But some tips from someone with dark brown hair who's had happy results with this kit for a couple of years now:

--Don't use the pick and cap thing--you can't get close enough to the roots. Instead, just use an old toothbrush to apply the highlight solution anywhere the sun would normally hit your hair. Apply the solution first where you want the most highlights because 5 minutes or more could pass before you get all the solution applied, so those areas you work on first will have the solution on longer than the rest of your hair.

--Don't forget the back of your hair! Hold up a hand mirror to a wall mirror to stroke the highlight solution on the back of your hair wherever the sun would normally hit.

--This kit makes a LOT of solution--you won't use it all, so don't be tempted to! Don't apply highlights underneath your hair or wherever the sun wouldn't hit it. If you do, it won't look natural.

--I apply highlights, set a timer for 10 minutes, then wash and blowdry my hair to see how it looks. If I want more highlights, I apply more solution, let it set for 10 minutes, then wash and dry again.. Just let the solution sit (it will foam up in the tray--that's okay) until you know you don't need it anymore.

btw, the shampoo and conditioner included in the kit is fabulous...your hair will feel like silk.

Enjoy!

column13: Amazing hair scissors. Professional hair cuts at home
column14:
I give hair cuts to all of my family members, and this started mostly because I was tired of paying $15 every couple months to keep my husbands hair in check. I watched how they did his hair, and went home with a pair of dollar store hair scissors and tried out a hair cut. It looked pretty good. I kept giving him hair cuts, which now people mistake as him getting a professional cut, but my scissors were wearing out and breaking every few months. That cost adds up. They are also not very sharp and often pull the hair a bit. I tried the equinox scissors out and I am amazed at the difference! These scissors are nicely weighted, not too light like the dollar store ones, and they are professional just like our old stylist used to use on everyone. The only down side is the finger holes are not big enough for my husband to use, but my fingers fit perfectly. So if you are getting a pair, be sure that your fingers are on the smaller side, otherwise equinox has a pair without the black rubber ring that allows bigger fingers to use them (I have a pair of their thinning scissors and his fingers fit just fine)

*I RECEIVED THIS PRODUCT AT A DISCOUNTED PRICE IN EXCHANGE FOR AN HONEST AND UNBIASED REVIEW. ALL OPINIONS ARE MY OWN

I use 5 drops every morning and every night after washing my face, then put on my moisturizer mixed with a few drops of 100% golden jojoba oil - my skin looks better than it did was I was in my teens and 20s.

column6: Cetaphil Daily Facial Moisturizer with Sunscreen SPF 50+, 1.7 Fluid Ounce
column13: Everything it Says it is and Does a Wonderful Job
column14:
ORIGINAL REVIEW (also read my update below): My only disappointment was that it even though it is absorbed quickly, it left the skin shiny. Please don't confuse "shiny" with "greasy" or "oily" for it is neither greasy or oily. The trick is learn how much you need (which turns-out to be very little) to protect your face and ears. The built-in pump meters-out very small amounts. 4 squirts gives you not quite a quarter-sized glob.. Just enough with a bit left over, which I apply to the back of my neck. I apply it after applying my aftershave lotion and am good for the day. I've slept without washing this off. It does not stain the bed linen.

UPDATE+++

I am on my second order of two tubes. I've learned that the resultant shininess was due to my simply using too much. With a little experimenting it appears that two squirts (half as much as originally suggested) and applying it more carefully gives me the same protection. Spending a few more minutes rubbing it into the skin also help reduce the shininess I observed when I first began using this product. A case (for me) when more is not better, or even necessary. Now knowing the "disappointment" was my own doing I've changed my overall rating to 5 stars.

column6: Neckline Slimmer & Toning System
column14: This device works muscles that a weight lifting headband won't. It also is light on the resistance side, but you can put two springs in at a time if you pay attention to what you are doing. This will increase the resistance to a more reasonable level for a man. My wife uses just one spring and that works fine for her. There are no quick fixes; you didn't obtain the loss of muscle tone in a week or a month and you won't correct the problem in a short time frame. This is still like any other workout routine; you must set a schedule and stick to it if you want too achieve any lasting results. You must also continue the routine after you achieve the results or you will regress to where you were. We have been using this device for a little over three weeks and can already see small improvements but we both realize it will take months of use to get the results we seek. I am a former bodybuilder and my wife is just a gorgeous woman who has had to do very little to maintain her looks. We are in our late 50s now and while we both still pass as early 40s we see signs of growing older and this little device is helping us regain the healthy looks to which we are accustomed. Plus we have converted a room of our house into a gym and are both back into body building, albeit at a much lighter level. So buy this gadget if you plan to use it diligently and you will eventually get the results you seek. If you aren't willing to put in the time and effort necessary to achieve the results, save your money and do nothing.

column6: Procter & Gamble Gillette Women's Razor and Handle with 2 Refills
column14: I was provided one of these Venus & Olay razors to test out via a program run by Venus. The five blade razor shaved the same width as my regular razor, however the blades seemed spaced closer together. The razor rinsed out easily, that along with no need for shaving cream makes for a quick shave for this razor. My favorite application of it is to shave my armpits in the sink when there is just no time to hop in the shower. It's also wonderful for shaving legs what ever the senario. I never had a problem with razor rash using this, which is typically a bit off an issue for me. The shave gel bars were a bit bulky at first, so the first few times I ever used it, I did have trouble with my bikini line, just getting the razor where I needed it was a little awkward so I ended up going back per the same areas with old razor. Still no shaving cream was needed then! The built in shave gel bars come off thick when the razor is fresh. I also noticed that I did not get as close of a shave as I am accostomed to using what I consider regular pressure, because of the way they razor slid atop the thick layer of shave gel. After using it a few different times that was no longer an issue. I had to get used to a different feel of the razor in my hand, change my technique a little, and the shave gel did not come off quite as think after the first few uses. After many uses the shave gel bars are almost gone. Now that they are thin and don't touch as great an are of my skin I think I will continue to use the razor for a bit as a normal razor with my regular shaving cream as the blades are still sharp and not yet needing to he replaced. Other people might not run in to this senario, I feel tht I rinsed off a lot of the gel bars just rinsing my hair out of the razor, however I have very thick hair. Overall this has given me the best shave experience, no razor burn, no need for additional shaving cream, less overall time spent shaving with this! The vanilla creme scent was hardly noticeableto me, so I can definitely say it was not over powering or unpleasant. The razor stick also came with a suction cup shower hook, I loved how petite it was, however I current don't keep my razor in the shower so it is of no use to me.

column6: Omiera Podiazole Nail Fungus Treatment, Toenail Fungus Treatment, Nails Anti Fungal, Nail Treatment - Restore nails to their natural state (1.0 fl oz)
column14:
I have one toe with a nail fungus on it. It is embarrassing trying to wear sandals in the summer, and I don't like to paint my toenails. A couple of years ago I had a fungus on my big toe and the doctor prescribed antifungal tablets to take for six months. I was told it was bad for your liver, so I only took it a couple of months and used some prescription antifungal cream on my toe at the same time. It finally went away and now I am faced with another toe with the dreaded toenail fungus.

I was very happy to see this over the counter Nail Fungus Treatment, since I don't want to go to the doctor or have my toenail removed. I am very hopeful that this Nail Fungus Treatment will work on my toe. On the package, there are no directions for using the Nail Fungus Treatment other than wash and dry the area before applying. It doesn't tell you how many times a day or how much to apply, so I have been applying it twice a day. The active ingredient is Undecylenic acid (15%), which is used as a topical antifungal agent. I have not experienced any burning, itching or stinging by using the Nail Fungus Treatment.

It is very important that you wash your nails each time very well and dry them before you apply the Nail Fungus Treatment. You need to continue treating your nail and trim off the infected nail until the infection is eliminated. Depending on your nail, you may need to use this topical nail treatment for up to six months, hopefully you will see improvements within one to three months.
I will update in a month on my nail progress.

I received this product at a discount in exchange for my honest and unbiased review.

column13: Turn any room into a tranquil space
column14:
This is one of the best impulse buys I've ever indulged in! I've had my for over a year and LOVE it. Being an asthmatic I have to be extremely careful with the scents I have in my environment. Though I love sweetly scented candles, they can sometimes make my asthma flare. This diffuser is a god send. Delivering whatever blends of natural oils I choose into the air it not only doesn't upset my asthma but soothes my body and mind. This tool makes for a great way to explore aromatherapy. Since it is diffused with water you don't have to worry about open flames of the oils being changed by heat.
Some of my personal favorite blends are:
Lavender + Peppermint (before bend or to relax)
Eucalyptus + Peppermint ( to soothe stress)
Clove Oil + Eucalyptus +Lemon + Cinnamon + Rosemary ( for when I'm under the weather)

Whether you are looking for a natural way to scent your home, or a way to explore the wonderful world of aromatherapy this is a fantastic product.

column6: Radical Bleach Kit
column14: This product had it's pros and cons for me. The actual bleach worked quickly and efficiently. I picked this product because it has a 40 volume developer and that is what salons have used on me in the past. The parts of my hair that had been bleached previously turned snow white and would have almost looked good without any type of toner. The regrowth in my hair was harder to bleach and did turn brassy. I did have a few problems with this product, however, and that is why I am only giving it three stars. I have thick, coarse hair that is a few inches below my shoulders. I used the highlighting cap and utilized all of the holes in the cap. The main issue I had with this product was that there was not enough bleach! If I had chosen to bleach all of my hair, I would've needed at least four kits to have enough product to do so. I still didn't have enough product to cover all of the hair that I needed done, so I focused the bleach on the top parts. This was extremely frustrating because I wasn't able to do the best job I could have done. If you have even slightly more hair than the average person, I would recommend getting two kits or buying the items separately. This kit ended up disappointing me. I was not expecting salon quality results, but I was expecting to have enough product to cover the 1/5 of my hair that I wanted to bleach.

column6: Nixoderm For Skin Problems Cream (Pack-3) 17.7 Grams
column13: My doctor had no recommendation to fix it besides another topical steroid which I tried and only made it worse. So I tried fixin
column14: I had perioral dermatitis after using a prescription topical steroid (for another health issue). My doctor told me that topical steroids shouldn't cause dermititis, but after Googling it I found out I'm not the only one to have that reaction. Unfortunately the dermatitis didn't go away when I stopped using the steroid. It stopped spreading, but the patches around my mouth and nose stayed. My doctor had no recommendation to fix it besides another topical steroid which I tried and only made it worse. So I tried fixing it on my own which lead me to try sooo many things. I tried supplements, water and exercise and healthy diet, going make up free, professional facials, masks, scrubs, washes, treatments, (DIY and store bought), etc. Some things helped a little, but would stop working after bit (like oatmeal and yogurt masks). I had it for almost a year and was losing my mind. Then, during my hundredth internet search, I found a post buried in some obscure forum that recommended Nixoderm. They said it burned bad, but it got rid of their perioral dermatitis. It was pretty cheap and at this point I had nothing to lose but more money so I gave it a go. And, yes, it does burn. The more you massage it in the more it burns. And if your skin condition is really bad it's only going to burn more. But after a week or so of using this the dermatitis was finally gone! I was happy and grateful! That was years ago but I recently started getting little skin colored bumps on my temples and jawline. This did help keep those weird bumps in line, but didn't get rid of them. Since it wasn't curing it I stopped (because it burns a lot for no result) and the bumps turned into red inflamed acne cyst clusters. So painful and ugly! Now at this point this product hasn't helped with the acne. But I have used it before on random pimples and it does help with that. So, for me, this is great for random pimples and perioral dermatitis but not quite for adult acne.

column6: Crest Pro-Health HD Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Healthier Mouth via Daily Two-Step System - 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
column13: Crest Pro-Health HD - Just okay for me
column14: I was given the opportunity to try Crest Pro Health HD for free - courtesy of Crest. It is a 2 step process - you use Step 1 toothpaste for one minute as this is your plaque removal process. You DO NOT rinse after Step 1 - you then use Step 2 for one minute as this is the polishing step (then you rinse). Says it will get your teeth up to 6 x's whiter - I only noticed maybe 1-2 x's whiter - if that. I used this system for exactly one month. I brushed twice a day. My likes? Totally fresh breath, very clean when I run my tongue over my teeth, some improvement on whitening, simple to use. My problems with this system? Gets kind of annoying to have to switch using different tubes of toothpaste, no major whitening noted, Step 2 doesn't taste great and it may irritate your gum line w/ the peroxide, I ran out of Step 1 in exactly 30 days and still had plenty of Step 2 so I couldn't do the whole system anymore, not nearly the whitening I was hoping for, I like to brush my tongue and gum line so I'd have to do this separately or with another toothpaste (not with this whitening product), and it's not sold at all stores. It does a great job of giving you a fresh from the dentist clean feeling, but the whitening? So, So.

column6: Amir Touch of Tan Moisturizer with Argan, 18 Fl Oz
column14:
After deciding during the brutal Boston winter that I needed a little bit of color, I considered my options. Going tanning is out of the question (paying my hard earned money for skin cancer? No thanks), and I was intimidated by the various spray tans, spray mousses, and other products out there that deliver some serious darkness (and you need to apply them with a "mitt"...I'm too low maintenance for that). I didn't want to walk into work the day after a self-tanning session with everyone asking me "How did you get so tan?...It's February", but I wanted a healthy glow, so I figured finding something that would offer a gradual tan would be my best bet. I also have a rather restrictive budget so I figured this was the perfect choice, at around 11 dollars for a decently large bottle. To top it off, I read all of the raving reviews on this product and thought it would be exactly what I was looking for.

Unfortunately, I was disappointed.

I had read enough reviews on tanning products that I knew the basics of how to use it properly: exfoliate thoroughly in the shower (I use Tree Hut Shea Sugar Scrub...love it), make sure you apply evenly and be careful around knees/elbows/ankles so it doesn't come out uneven, wash hands thoroughly afterwards so you don't spread the brown color everywhere, don't put on clothes for a while so it can all absorb, etc. I followed the instructions carefully every time, and used it religiously every other day for about three weeks.

At the end of the three weeks, I was rather disappointed. Although this makes for a great moisturizer and smells great (hence the two stars), my "tan" was virtually nonexistent. I was just as pale as I had been three weeks earlier trudging through the four feet of snow in my driveway. So if you're like me and you're looking for a gradual tan that will give you a nice glow, I suggest you keep looking. If you're just looking for a good moisturizer in a lovely pumpbottle, by all means buy this one.

column13: I'm not a heavy user...but these fit the machines they are for. However a back bar rubs the roller during use = annoying.
column14: Fine as replacement heads. I have hard time tellng if there is any real difference in performance between the so called grit sizes. I clean mine with a SOFT or EXTRA soft tooth brush after every use. I just remove and brush down into the bath sink and then wash any dust on down the drain. I also place a thick bath mat or towel on floor before using these in the machine. This avoids dust getting ground into your carpets or spread about the room as much too. I almost went with a cheaper brand because the rollers are larger and there is no annoying back support or elongated back side that gets in the way of the rollers when you press a bit too much or actually very little at times while in use. But I didn't and went with this and bought the gray so called man's machine. The mini palm sized version...these rollers fit the longer versions too. Anyway I am satisfied with the rollers but see no difference between them in actual use. Maybe some looking at them but they all seem to do the same exact job and results. If you clean them with the tooth brush after every use you should get far more uses out of each roller than if you choose not to. My guess is like 2 maybe 3 times more use per roll. I also use the tooth brush always SOFT to clean the flat pedi file like paddles too and I had one of the better ones last me over 2 years. Sometimes the cheaper ones give up the glue to the board sooner...but look for an extra soft or even ask you dentists office if they have the super soft or soft brushes next time you visit. I'm happy overall with the refills and the machine except that back bar that occasionally rubs the rollers....that is annoying...and because of that the one star off.

column6: Shikakai Powder 3.5oz (100g) - Hesh Pharma
column13: My hair was thining and shedding at an amazing rate. To add to my problem
column14: This is the first time writing a comment, on a product.  I always had thick hair, lots of shedding over the years.  I thought it was due to  the relaxers I used for so many years.  My hair was thining and shedding at an amazing rate. To add to my problem, I began graying which added another chemical to my damage hair.I decided to give  néem, shikakai, Aritha and Amla a try.  I began this journey May 30 2015., I trim my hair, off approximately 3 inches.  I had my hair in a proactive style,(braids) for two months.  I noticed my hair grew 1.5 inches in first month.  I removed the braid, my hair grew but The most amazing thing. I noticed the shedding, decreased, vertually stopped, just a few strands of hair in the Comb.  The mixture is messy but it is worth it.  My mixture  consist of Amla powder, neem powder, shikakai powder,  Aretha powder mixed about 1 tsp full of each, in Amal oil and coconut oil.  Combined all together in a paste.  Part your hair into  four sections and apply the mixture to your hair.  Leave on for 45-60 mins; rinse your hair well in the shower work best. Use a shampoos of your choice to remove the excess power and residue.  My hair is soft and managable.  Hope this information helps.  I plan on using weekly, for the next year..

column6: Desert Essence - Thoroughly Clean Face Wash
column13: Stop washing your face with acid. And get a foamer.
column14:
This works just as good as Neutrogena's Oil Free Acne Stress Control, without all of the chemicals. I'm almost 30 and started to question why I was still washing my face with acid. I figured it was time to get away from the acne washes. My face feels clean and fresh after using this. I use it once a day (in the morning) and use Cetaphil before bed so as not to over-irritate. Good for back, chest, really anywhere that is oily. It's a potent cleanser--a little goes a long way. If I use 2 pumps with a foamer every day, this bottle will probably last me until I'm 60. In my opinion, you have to use this with a simple, cheap foamer. I washed one from my old face washes out and have been re-using it and it works perfectly. If you don't use a foamer, you're just going to be wasting it.

Positive: Cheap considering how long it will last. No chemicals, but I'm not an expert on that. I mean, I figure it has to have less than the other crap I've used. It cleans my skin really well without making it chapped, dry, flaky, etc. Actually, I think the Cetaphil for oily skin is more drying than this is.

Negative: While it doesn't dry my skin out, it is potent, and you shouldn't over-do it with this. 2 pumps with a foamer.

Neutral: It does make my face a little red. It's not a chapped or irritated red, it's literally just like my skin is a little flushed after I use it. Your milage may vary.

column6: Frankincense, Myrrh & Holiday Blend Essential Oil Gift Set :: Pure Undiluted (3 x 1oz)
column13: One oil was pure, one was not.
column14: A drop test, which tests the purity of essential oils, proved that the myrrh oil in this package is not pure. In a drop test, a true essential oil will evaporate completely, leaving no trace. The myrrh left an oily stain, meaning it's been mixed with another oil. However the frankincense tested pure. When I contacted the company, they expressed surprise and gratitude for bringing the problem to them, and said they'd look into their supplier, which means at least they're on top of it, as opposed to other companies who just insist their product is pure when it isn't'. That's why I gave them three stars instead of one, on the off chance that the impure oil was not their fault, but the fault of their supplier.

column6: New Double Edge Safety Razor Satin Black Finish Longer Heavier Package Include 10 Stainless Steel Blades and a Leather Pouch
column13: Nice Razor at a Nice Price
column14: Okay, let me preface this review by saying that I am a confirmed straight razor shaver, love them, will never leave them. That doesn't mean that I don't like a little variety in my morning shave and have in the past used a DE razor on occasion. I've been on the lookout for a new DE and thought this would fill the need for me. It shipped and arrived promptly and securely packaged. My 1st impression of this razor was favorable, I like the look of it and really like the black satin finish. It has a nice heft to it and is comfortable in my hand compared to a few other DE's I've used. After going through my normal straight razor face prep I lathered up and started my shave. I'll admit my DE technique is lacking especially since it's been awhile since I've used one. It didn't matter, this is a very smooth shaving razor. The weight is distributed right wear it needs to be. The weight of the head is near perfect in my opinion, I didn't need any pressure on my shaving strokes other than just the weight of the head. The handle provides a nice grip even when wet so no issues there either. I had a very nice 2 pass shave without any nicks or cuts that left my face smooth, didn't need to go 1 more pass or even touch any spots up. For those who say that it's only the blade that gives you a smooth clean shave I beg to differ. Try using a DE that has little to no weight in the head or the weight is not distributed correctly, then tell me it's just the blade, The razor makes all the difference and this one does just what it should. After shaving I cleaned the razor and looked closely at the finish as some of the reviews stated the black finish "washed" off or whatever, Not on mine, looks just as good as it did when I opened the box. I will keep using this razor, it won't be my daily shaver as I still like my straights too much but I can guarantee you it's not going to be collecting dust on a shelf. My conclusion is this is a very nice razor at a very affordable price, I do recommend it.
