column14:
My poor young daughter was blessed with course and easy to tangle hair. She is nearly seven and we have been trying all sorts of detanglers out there and none actually did anything more than wet the hair down and scent it.

This is different. I know this is a leave in conditioner but please you need to try it off label as a detangler!!! I just put it in a spray bottle and put it in her hair after a bath on wet hair, or on dry hair while I am styling it. It works equally as well on both wet and dry hair.

She has naturally curly/wavy hair and Infusium sort of separates and defines her curls. Somehow it adds body (So it does not weight the hair down at all) and now receives compliments on how her hair shimmers. (No glitter or oilyness, just natural shimmer) where as before it was dull.

She is a swimmer and goes to swimming lessons and such in a chlorinated pool for nearly four hours a week. This stuff keeps her hair strong and healthy looking. I even use it in my hair because it adds natural shimmer and body. We have been using it for several months now and there is no need to try another type of product.

column13: Wow, this stuff really works for clearing out smelly odors!
column14:
As far as "deodorizing" oils go, this is one heck of a slam dunk. I share a house with two of my buddies and needless to say, it can get a tidbit smelly around the house. I bought a couple essential oil diffusers to help make it smell a little more "women friendly" and while I have found plenty of oils that can help mask the smell, this is the only one that seems to truly deodorize the air.

I also mixed up some actual deodorant to try it out and it worked really well. I didn't use the recipe they provided, I just went all mad scientist and mixed a couple carrier oils, water, and this and it worked for the entire day. I wasn't sure if maybe I just didn't notice so I asked my buddies and my girlfriend and everyone said I didn't smell at all.

Overall, I think this is a really awesome oil and would recommend it to anyone. I was lucky enough to be given a discount because they are changing their labeling and we're trying to get rid of the old stock but even at the full price, this is worth it 100%.

Also, if you're new to Plant Therapy products, you should know that they are very high quality and are quickly becoming one of my favorite oil manufacturers.

column6: Neutrogena Wave Sonic Power Cleanser with 14 Foaming Pads
column13: Amazing, a decent little product in \this day and age.\""
column14:
My daughter bought me one of these at a local drug store. I have been using it for a couple of weeks and really, as some other people have said, I wonder how the high-priced gadgets like it can be much better? I am 75 years old and have milia (little hard white bumps) all over my face plus deep lines as well as finer ones. I saw an improvement right away, but checked with my daughter to see what she though. She said my color was brighter and more uniform, no more dark spots. Roughness is gone. The top layer of skin over the milia gradually gets abraded away, and they either come out on their own or with just a bit of scratching or rubbing (be gentle!). The deep lines really are shallower, because the outer layers of essentially dead skin are gone.

I was just looking at the reviews, thinking maybe there was something even better, but now am convinced I won't need to look further. Some of the suggestions in the reviews are helpful, too. The thing I do to save money on the refill scrubbers is just set it somewhere to dry for the day and then use it again in the shower, so I get two uses. I suppose eventually I'll catch some dread disease, but so far, so good, and I don't think I'm in any danger.

If you are wondering whether this type of thing works, try this one. It has such a low price, and I've never heard anyone was hurt by one...

column6: Crest 3D White Brilliance Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Deep Cleansing via Daily Two-Step System, 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
column14:
I'm very excited to write this review for those who are looking for a gentle, yet effective whitening system! I was fortunate to receive this product free to try through Crest and BzzAgent. I was so excited to join this campaign to test out this new whitening system! I've used all kinds of whitening strips and gels in the past, and while they work, they would also leave my teeth very sensitive. This Daily cleansing and whitening system has not given me any side effects whatsoever. Even after the first use, your mouth feels sqeaky clean, and already a shade whiter. I've been using this product for a few weeks now, and I'm very pleased with the results! I love that I can use it twice a day with zero sensitivity.
The only down side for me, is I have very sensitive gums. It states right on the label that it may leave small white spots on the gums, but that's normal and they will go away. This is true, you will notice that if you have sensitive gums. I have only noticed that reaction though, when I've had a cut from brushing too hard and then it stains that area. It does go away shortly after, however. Just brush gently, and be patient, and you will love the results. Plus, it tastes great! The biggest reason I never whiten with peroxide is because it tastes horrible. The whitening agent in this system is peroxide, but it tastes good! I hope this review helped, I'm glad I gave this whitening system a try! This is a great product!
-Melissa

column6: Dove Men +Care Shampoo
column13: Don't Expect Miracles, but Dove Men+Care Seems to Add Some Volume
column14:
I am a middle aged male with very fine hair. In fact, at this point, I am still happy to have any hair on my head, let alone a thick mane of hair. I am always on the hunt for shampoos that add volume, and Dove Men+Care Shampoo, with caffeine and \\\Oxycharge\\\\\" technology, promises to do just that.

I have been using the shampoo for more than two weeks, and I can report that Dive Men+Care does add some volume. I don't need to use very much to get plenty of lather, and I just let the shampoo sit on my scalp for two or three minutes before rinsing off. The caffeine is supposed to promote growth and the oxycharge technology removes oil and residue. The shampoo, which comes in a large 25.4 ounce bottle, has a masculine cologne-like odor.

While I am not expecting to have a full head of thick hair, Dove Men+Care does seem to help. I am encouraged by the results, and will continue to use so I can continue to be a major chick magnet."

column13: Awesome products, but beware... Very loud!
column14: It works really great and I love that it has a toothbrush and a waterpik flosser and spots to store the extra flosser heads, as well as the bonus travel case for the toothbrush. I am a big fan of waterpik water flossers and love using them, so I was excited to get this and also have a waterpik brand toothbrush. I really like that it has a feature where it does 30 second intervals for each four quadrants of the mouth and has two speed settings. I also like that the flosser comes with so many different heads, including an orthodontic tip. The reason for knocking out a star is that it is EXTREMELY loud. Now, I have a cordless portable waterpik glossed, as well and that one is very quiet compared this. The water flosser sounds like a very loud machine, and you can hear it throughout the entire house. The toothbrush is loud, too but the flosser is top notch loud. Other than that, they work good and well, it works... so aside from noise, I still like it a lot and it's not enough to make me dislike the product altogether because I do love the brand and how great they work.

column14: I received this set as a trial as part of BzzAgent. The first step tastes a lot like the blue sparkle tooth paste that I used as a kid. You brush for 1 minute with it and spit but do not rinse. This part leaves my mouth feeling rather gross.... Then you apply step 2 for a minute and it tastes like hydrogen peroxide gel. After this step is completed rinse. It's really simple, works really well and it doesnt seem to add any extra time to my morning or nightly routine. The one problem I do have with it is my teeth seem overly sensitive now. I expected that because I have problems with it anyway. Over all the product is worth it. It does a great job and is quick and simple. It's great for people with very crooked teeth like me because it works better than a whitening toothpaste and doesnt need to conform to fit your teeth like strips or mouth plates.

column13: Venus & Olay makes for a quick shave!
column14: I was provided one of these Venus & Olay razors to test out via a program run by Venus. The five blade razor shaved the same width as my regular razor, however the blades seemed spaced closer together. The razor rinsed out easily, that along with no need for shaving cream makes for a quick shave for this razor. My favorite application of it is to shave my armpits in the sink when there is just no time to hop in the shower. It's also wonderful for shaving legs what ever the senario. I never had a problem with razor rash using this, which is typically a bit off an issue for me. The shave gel bars were a bit bulky at first, so the first few times I ever used it, I did have trouble with my bikini line, just getting the razor where I needed it was a little awkward so I ended up going back per the same areas with old razor. Still no shaving cream was needed then! The built in shave gel bars come off thick when the razor is fresh. I also noticed that I did not get as close of a shave as I am accostomed to using what I consider regular pressure, because of the way they razor slid atop the thick layer of shave gel. After using it a few different times that was no longer an issue. I had to get used to a different feel of the razor in my hand, change my technique a little, and the shave gel did not come off quite as think after the first few uses. After many uses the shave gel bars are almost gone. Now that they are thin and don't touch as great an are of my skin I think I will continue to use the razor for a bit as a normal razor with my regular shaving cream as the blades are still sharp and not yet needing to he replaced. Other people might not run in to this senario, I feel tht I rinsed off a lot of the gel bars just rinsing my hair out of the razor, however I have very thick hair. Overall this has given me the best shave experience, no razor burn, no need for additional shaving cream, less overall time spent shaving with this! The vanilla creme scent was hardly noticeableto me, so I can definitely say it was not over powering or unpleasant.

column13: Great option as a more natural cleanser!
column14: Edited to add: I've had this bottle for almost 5 months and its still not empty. Granted I only use it 2-3 times a week at most, but it takes the *tiniest* bit to work and I still love it. Very happy to have this!  This is by far my favorite cleanser that I've tried in a long time. I have been slowly making the switch to more natural options in terms of my skincare and my household and this was offered at a promotional rate, so I had to try it. I like it so much more than I expected! I stopped using cleansers on my face about a year ago and my face completely cleared up once I did, so I'm always hesitant to throw things off. BUT somedays you just need to get that *clean* feeling that only soaps provide. After a busy day outside with the kids (I live in Florida), or a really good workout, or after you've been sick for a couple days and just have that icky feeling. Water alone is a good cleaner for most days, but this has definitely become my "I want to get my face REALLY clean" cleanser. It cleans well without completely stripping my face of everything and doesn't leave my face a dry wasteland like "regular" cleansers do. It smells good, it lathers just enough but not a crazy amount, and it only takes a teensy tiny bit to work. About half the size of a pea and you are good to do your whole face and neck. An excellent value, especially in regards to exposing yourself to less chemicals and nasty stuff! I received this product at a reduced cost and/or free in exchange for my honest and unbiased review.

column6: Sweet Almond Oil for Skin, Hair and Face - Large 16oz - WITH PUMP + FREE Recipe eBook! - All Natural Sensual Massage Oil - Use with Essential Oils and Aromatherapy as a Carrier and Base oil
column13: Great oil, especially for the price.
column14:
Product arrived quickly. Came with a pump and a flip top, which if very convenient for use. It also lists the manufacturing date and expiration date (3 years, which is a surprise. I didn't think the shelf life was that long for Sweet Almond Oil.) This is also a good price for such a large bottle.

Sweet Almond Oil is a great oil. It's "light" and literally has no scent. It's supposed to sooth dry skin and irritated areas. I have sensitive, allergic, reactive, rosacea skin. Have to be really careful what I use on it. Only use carrier oils to moisturize. The last week, or so, I've been having a lot of bumpy, rashy skin--especially on my cheeks. I thought I might be having an allergic reaction to some serums I'd made. (One drop of an essential oil blend in a teaspoon of carrier oil--a 1% dilution, which is appropriate for face.) I actually figured out that it's not the essential oil blends, it's another allergy season starting (I get this way with tree and grass pollen in the spring and ragweed in the fall.) I've used the Pure Acres Farm Sweet Almond Oil and so far, no problem. My skin stayed smooth and pink (good for me.) It also absorbed quickly--a plus for summer time.

Another way that I use carrier oils is to protect my skin in the winter. Before I go out in the elements, I always put a few drops of oil on my face. It also helps protect your skin from the dryness in the house when the heat is on. I use those few drops on my face several times a day--when I wake up, after my shower and any other time I think of it, or my face feels dry.

Another thing that I want to do is make a herb oil infusion and make my own lip balm. For a lot of people, Sweet Almond Oil is the oil of choice for lip balm. I've just started to make herb infused oils (which are easy.) I've made salves for first aid and pain, so far. Next attempt will be lip balm. It's just some infused oil, beeswax and essential oils to flavor (which is optional.) If it's ofinterest, you can do a web search and come up with a lot of easy recipes.

column13: I'm giving the Murad Balancing Moisturizer 3 stars. The ...
column14:
I'm giving the Murad Balancing Moisturizer 3 stars.
The Pros: it does not irritate my skin. It goes on lightweight. It absorbs quickly. It also appears to be making my pores smaller or appear smaller in my T-zone, after applying once a day for a few days.
The Cons: The ingredients to achieve this. In doing research on women's hormones and looking at this product's contents, several ingredients are endocrine blockers. I won't go into details about endocrine disrupting ingredients because there's plenty of information out there if you're interested. I'm mentioning it here because had I done more research before purchasing, I'd have moved on and looked for a more hormone-friendly product.
As always, it comes down to personal choice/preference. For me, I've found that I want something that will be harmonious with my body more than I want the beauty bonuses it promises.

column6: Just For Me Hair Milk Detangler Treatment, Pre Wash Softening 8 oz
column13: Good product for thick, coarse, hard-to-comb hair
column14:
We're a curly-haired family; I'm of Italian ancestry, my wife is South Indian, and our daughter is the resultant mix. We all have coarse, thick, curly hair (well, what's left of it, in my case). We decided to give this a try to see if its claims of making hair-care easier for people like us panned out.

For my wife and for me, the product works as advertised. You apply it to your hair while dry, just before wetting your hair for shampooing. It conditions the hair well (it's basically a conditioner that you use first, instead of last), and makes it much easier to get a comb through the hair, without leaving hair greasy.

One setback is that the product makes it pretty clear that it can irritate the eyes, and should be kept away from children. So my wife vetoed the original plan to try it on our four year-old, who whines (and sometimes screams) her way through any attempt to comb her hair. We'll give it a try on her in the future, but for the grownups in our house, it works as advertised.

column6: NYX Jumbo Eye Pencil Shadow Liner 604 Milk
column14:
Nyx Jumbo pencil in "Milk" is absolutly fantastic. In the photos I've posted I used the product from lid to brow bone. I makes the whites whiter, and the colors brighter.

The jumbo pencil glides on smoothly when you apply and is quite creamy. Once you smooth it a bit with your finger you're ready to go. Pat your eyeshadow on top to set the cream and once you've done an initial layer of shadow you can begin blending out the colors or lack thereof as needed.

The pencil sharpens easily as the shell is made of plastic. All you need is a jumbo pencil sharpener. If you prefer it in a pot all you have to do is microwave or use a blow dryer to melt the product down into whatever container you'd like. (Use caution)

I have bought this product multiple times and will continue to do so in the future.

column14:
It's been about 5 years since I've used regular deodorant. My main concerns about deodorants are parabens, aluminum, and strong fragrances.

I replaced deodorant with a crystal body deodorant roll-on. I also use the body stick. I decided to try the roll-on since I was very happy with the crystal stick.

Pros:
No fragrance.
Goes on clear.
Really does control odor.
Does not contain parabens or aluminum.
Does not stain clothes.

Cons:
If you have a tendency to perspire heavily, this product won't work for you.
If you have a tendency towards developing strong body odors this product may not work for you.

Will I use this product again? Yes this will continue to be my product of choice.

Who should use this product? This product works for people who do not perspire heavily and who are seeking alternatives to deodorant.

Beauty 4 1 1 N N I think this has worked well for me, and I like the ingredients I've been using this in the morning for a couple of weeks now. It has been gentle, moisturizing, and non-irritating to my sometimes sensitive skin. I don't notice much of a scent to it and it has not caused me to break out. It absorbs quickly and does not interfere with the subsequent application of makeup (I use it after toner and before moisturizer).

It is hard to tell if I am seeing a benefit from this, but I actually think that's the point. This contains a lot of antioxidants (including, for example, vitamins A, C, and E and green tea extract), which are supposed to protect against sun damage. (They do not take the place of a good sunscreen, and I have been wearing an SPF 50 sunscreen under my makeup as well.) If you do not see an increase in fine lines and/or discoloration, then this product may very well be doing its job.

I like all the plant extracts in the ingredients, and I love that this doesn't contain any artificial dyes or fragrances (you can see the ingredients list if you scroll down the product page). My teen son was thrilled to receive this set. Phoenix is his favorite scent in the AXE line and, as his mother, I don't find it offensive like some of the horrific things his teen friends wear. This scent would, in my opinion, smell great on a grown man as well. It doesn't scream "I'm a teenager" like some scents do.
As for the products, he has worn the AXE solid antiperspirant for years and it has always kept him dry and smelling great. The body wash works well, and the scent does linger a bit, but it does contain Sodium Laureth Sulfate (SLES) for those who are looking to avoid it. Finally, the spray... ohhhhhh the spray... it seems to be a *must* for any young teenager. It is strong but in our house the rule is, it must be sprayed outside the house, away from the body, and then walked into. This isn't for some great health reason, it is for my poor nose when it is stuck in a small vehicle with him I don't want gag on a fragrance bomb. One of my favorite things about the spray is how it locks so it can't accidentally go off in a drawer and coat the inside and everything else inside the drawer. This has happened on more than one occasion with a different spray.

Overall, this is a great set. It is labeled as a "gift box" but it is really just these three items in the cardboard box pictured above. column6: Organic Lavender Essential Oil. USDA Organic. 100% Pure, Undiluted, Therapeutic Grade
column13: The strongest lavender I have run across. This little bottle should last a long time even with daily use!
column14:
If you're new to essential oils, a good Lavender essential oil should be one of your first purchases.

Lavender oil can be used for:
Muscle aches and stress
Sun burns/other burns
Acne treatment
Wound healing
Foot bath
and most importantly, it can be used in a diffuser to help with calming and sleep and I gotta say, it really works for putting me to sleep. I've always had trouble falling asleep but with the scent of Lavender in the air I am out like a light.

Now I gotta be honest, there are much bigger bottles out there for around the same price as this oil and while there are many awesome ones (Check out Majestic Pure for some awesome oils) this is by far one of the strongest lavenders I have ever run across. With that in mind, I have no doubt that this bottle will last every bit as long as a 4oz bottle simply because you don't have to use nearly as much.

I was lucky enough to get a discount because they are currently changing their packaging/labeling and had to deplete their old stock, but this isn't my first time buying from Plant Therapy and their oils are consistently great!. I love this stuff and at full price its still a killer deal!

Not sure if this was an oversight, but it really kills the mood of the product, at least for me anyway.

I was expecting a cream that smelled like tea tree oil, which I love, but I couldn't detect the fragrance at all. I got this product to use on my cyclical cystic acne, which I get on my chin. I will say, in the time I've been using it, I have seen a little bit of lessening of acne bumps, but nothing major. I will continue to use this, and see if it makes a big difference say after 2 months or so.

column6: E.l.f. Acne Fighting Foundation Ivory, 1.21 Fluid Ounce
column13: My undertones are definitely pink but I'm not pale and freckled like most redheads
column14:
I have auburn hair and fair coloring. My undertones are definitely pink but I'm not pale and freckled like most redheads. This was a little yellow for my skin. But it blends in just fine so no biggie. And now that it's the peak of summer it's a little light, but I'm sure it'll be a great shade once fall rolls around. I recently got a sudden adult acne breakout which I've never had before. So in attempt to narrow down what caused it it I threw out all of my makeup brushes and my facial makeup. But after about two weeks of going makeup free I couldn't stand it anymore. My face was only getting worse and seeing just my reflection in windows was enough to make me want to cry. Which is how I ended up buying this. It isn't a very heavy cover up, but it does just fine. You can still see my blemishes (I'm not sure there's a makeup in the world that could hide those), but it hides all the red blotchiness. While it isn't healing my acne, it also isn't aggravating it either. Which is all I could ask for from such a cheap foundation. I use a beauty sponge to apply it all over my face and then I use the residual foundation in the cap as concealer and apply it with a concealer makeup brush. I wash all of my makeup application tools AT LEAST once a week. I've started using an acne treatment with benzoyl peroxide which makes my face CRAZY flaky and dry, even combined with a high quality moisturizer. And if I have a particularly flaky day with this on my face it can look pretty gross. Since my skin appears to be normal color it just looks like I'm shedding like a lizard. So if you're using a treatment that causes your skin to flake sometimes just be careful putting this makeup over it because it can look kinda gross. If you can stand it going makeup free might be better. But if I'm having a good non-flaky day this is just fine and disguises the wreck my face has become.

UPDATE: After using this for a long time it's my favorite foundation. I went to a dermatologist and got my acne under control. It was a rough road but it's gone now. So with acne free skin this is fabulous for me. It looks so natural on my face. I can apply it with clean fingers, or a beauty sponge, or a foundation brush. All applications look very natural. If I want a more makeup-y look I sometimes use a powder over it. Otherwise I just leave it be and use concealer to touch up trouble spots. Looks like my skin is just naturally smooth. Love it.under control. It was a rough road but it's gone now. So with acne free skin this is fabulous for me. It looks so natural on my face. I can apply it with clean fingers, or a beauty sponge, or a foundation brush. All applications look very natural. If I want a more makeup-y look I sometimes use a powder over it. Otherwise I just leave it be and use concealer to touch up trouble spots. Looks like my skin is just naturally smooth. Love it.

column14:
Free product provided for evaluation and review.

This is somewhat pleasant to use. I like the effects of the mask better than the experience of putting it on and using it.

My first impression was that the jar was rather small, but it really only takes a tiny bit. There are several applications in the jar. It smells medicinal. I don't care for the smell but it's tolerable.

Even though it is clay, it is very moisturizing and leaves skin feeling very soft, and not at all tight. It does seem to brighten skin some, and it leaves my pores nice and tight and looking small. I do like that.

Directions are to put a thick layer on, and to leave it for 15-30 minutes. It states it might tingle some, because of the glycolic acid, but I did not experience that. You can rub it in small circles as it dries to exfoliate a bit. I didn't find it all that exfoliating though.

It does rinse off quite easily with just warm water.

column6: Neutrogena Healthy Skin Face Lotion SPF 15, 2.5 Fl. Oz
column14:
I didn't buy this lotion on Amazon, but I did purchase it at my local drug store. Being a faithful neutrogena customer, I thought I would give it a try because I used to use a different moisturizer (for combination skin) that had a pleasant odor and felt light on my face while also feeling like it is hydrating my skin. I figured I would feel this way about this as it is a similar product, but with a higher spf and features the word "healthy" which catches my attention.
First, the pump on the bottle barely pushes any out. I use a generous amount usually but this was a dismal pump at best. The lotion had a very strong scent which was off putting for me. I decided to apply it anyhow, as I am not one who is typically sensitive to strong scents. The absolute worst part of this product which made me demote from 2 to 1 stars is IT STINGS! My face felt like it was scraped across pavement. Keep in mind, I have a high tolerance to this type of thing. No known allergic reactions to any fragrances or anything else. It only lasts about 2 minutes, but it is a very unpleasant 2 minutes. I tried to rub it off immediately after but the stinging sensation was already in full swing.

I have only used it twice at this point. I used it immediately after purchase, and then after I got home and removed my makeup and washed my face, I applied it a second time. Both times I had the same results. I sit here typing this only about 15 minutes after applying and the tingling is still persisting ever so slightly in my cheeks. I will admit, however, that my skin feels slightly more hydrated, but it is borderline sticky.

Overall, I DO NOT recommend. If you like Neutrogena then I strongly suggest going with the other moisturizers that they have.

PS the bottle suggests reapplying every 2 hours.........Even if this didn't have the side effects, I don't really want a moisturizer that needs that frequent of a reapplication.

LOVE YOUR SKIN! STAY AWAY!!

column6: June Jacobs Anti-Aging Blemish Control Foaming Cleanser 150ml/5.0oz
column13: hard to find a product that addresses both of these concerns!
column14:
I'm at that stage of life where I am thinking about breakouts and anti-aging so it is nice to have a product that combines both types of benefits (usually you get one or the other, but not both).

This is a foaming cleanser and must be used with the pump. Like all foaming cleansers, it is rather thin and relies on the pump to create volume (through injection of air bubbles). The texture is really too thin for my taste, but I still think the product is effective.

I generally use this twice a day -- in the morning and then to remove makeup in the evening. It gets most, but not all, of my liquid foundation. In this, it is pretty typical of other cleansers I have used. I will say, though, that I have been rather stressed lately (moved to a new house plus my dog has been sick) and yet my skin is clearer than it has been for a long while. So this is definitely helping. (I suspect the salicylic acid and tea tree oil are largely responsible.)

Here is the full ingredients list:

ACTIVE INGREDIENT: SALICYLIC ACID 1%

INACTIVE INGREDIENTS: Water, Decyl Glucoside, Glycerin, Propanediol, Lactic Acid, Malic Acid, Tea Tree Leaf Oil, Camphor, Menthol, Turmeric Root Extract, Globularia Alypum Leaf Extract, Broccoli Extract, Willow Bark Extract, Red Tea Leaf Extract, Green And White Tea Leaf Extract, Goji Berry Fruit Extract, Pomegranate Extract, Grape Seed Extract, Algae Extract, Allantoin, Panthenol, Hyaluronic Acid, Sodium Levulinate, Sodium Hydroxide, Sodium Anisate, Sodium Phytate, Alginate, Arnica Montana Extract, Sunflower Seed Oil, Matricaria Flower Extract, Fragrance, Citral, Eugenol, Linalool, Limonene.

I love that it contains no artificial dyes. It does contain a fragrance ingredient (no idea if it's natural or not; truthfully, I don't notice the scent much because I am hard-pressed to describe it, even after using 3/4 of the bottle). I love all the antioxidants (from pomegranate, goji berries, green tea, etc.), which should (in combination with a good SPF product) help fight free radical damage. This contains hyaluronic acid and so is likely not a vegan product (most hyaluronic acid used in industry is generated as a byproduct of poultry processing, although there are some plant-based alternatives).

This rinses off cleanly and has not irritated my skin. It's more difficult to describe the anti-aging effects since I am mostly using this as prevention rather than treatment, except to say that the antioxidants and hyaluronic acid (a polymer that hangs on to moisture and thus helps with fine lines) are found in a lot of anti-aging preparations.

Overall, though, I'm quite happy with this product.ea, etc.), which should (in combination with a good SPF product) help fight free radical damage. column6: 4 Way Shiny Block
column13: Budget priced nail buffing block, works okay as long as you don't expect multiple uses out of it.
column14:
The buffer works as advertised, and by using the 4 sides in the correct sequence of grit, I was able to get rid of the ridges and eventually get the nail plate shiny. The product I received does NOT have the sides labelled as the product photo shows, I had to discover by trial and error which order to use the four sides in. There were no instructions, either. The packaging looked like it is intended for professional nail salon techs to use at work; they would know without needing to read labels which sides are which in order of grit.
The quality seems to be not very good, in that I was only able to get three or four uses before the grit on the #1 and #2 sides was pretty much worn off. But maybe that's normal? I would assume that a nail salon would only use this buffing block on one client, then discard it, right? So maybe it would be actually wasteful to make them more durable. Maybe they're meant to be as disposable as a a cotton swab.

column6: Medi-Rub Foot Massager 2000 Plus
column14:
Minor miracle. My MIL actually likes this among all her other gadgets. Since she is so selective, I bought a used one for trial after cleaning it with Lysol and rubbing alchohol; it's absolutely worth the money but $230 is a bit steep. It is very well made in USA with a 10-foot cord, unlike most of the imported cheap stuff, such as Homedic variety.

She has severe diabetes and leg swelling. After just 20 minutes in high (II) mode, she detected scratchy/itchy feelings in her feet. I advised her to do it 3x/day (she can go extreme) for starter. Her swelling has gone down on her first day.

She also liked it when I shifted it on a slant mode so she could do her lower calves. Its a keeper.

Suggestion for improvement: one of the competitors has variable speed, not just 2-speed. A built-in timer would be nice. It's noisy and does vibrate (the correct term is oscillation), so put it on top of a rug or towel but not a tile or hardwood floor.

Similar products made by the same manufacturer are: Jeanie Rub, Maxi Rub and Medi Massager.

column13: I don't see any SPF or Matrixyl 3000 in the ingredient list, has no tint
column14:
How do you compare the hundreds of skin care products? As a regular tester, I've arrived at a list of key considerations. I hope these are helpful to you!

~ Fragrance: Almost none.
~ Feel during application: Smooth, in a thick sort of way. Sort of a makeup primer feel, like it wants to fill in imperfections.
~ Feel after absorption: Smooth, moist, like a makeup primer has been applied.
~ Is it best for a certain skin type?: Should be okay for all, except maybe acne-prone.
~ Is it tested on animals?: Unknown.
~ Packaging: Nice-looking 2-oz airless pump.
~ Immediate cosmetic effects:* Leaves my oily skin a little more matte, which is nice, but left my skin feeling very heavy after makeup was applied. Good makeup primer. It does contain ACETYL HEXAPEPTIDE-8 (Argireline) which is a decent wrinkle reducer but only on a short-acting basis - in other words cosmetic.
~ Potential long-term effectiveness:* Sunscreen is one of the best things you can give your skin. However, despite the claims of 25SPF, I can find no sunscreens in this product. Cyclohexasiloxane, one of the top 3 ingredients, is listed in Canada as harmful to aquatic life. I also fail to see the advertised Matryxl 3000 anywhere in the ingredients. This is basically a bunch of skin conditioners with a few fruit extracts thrown in. Last in the ingredient list are tocopheryl acetate and retinyl palmitate, probably in tiny amounts.

This product contains no tint, no sunscreen unless I'm completely missing something, no effective anti-aging ingredients, and primarily a bunch of cosmetic silicones. How this qualifies as a BB cream (typically thought of as a moisturizer, sunscreen, makeup, and skin care all in one) is beyond me.

*Know the difference between cosmetic and long-term effects: Cosmetic effects are immediate and only present when the product has been applied recently - just like makeup. Long-term effects take longer to see and should remain when you stop using the product (but don't when you find something effective - your skin needs continuing support). The ideal product would be both cosmetically and long-term effective, but it's more realistic to expect a formula to tilt towards one or the other.

column6: Olay Regenerist Micro-sculpting Eye Swirl
column14:
I've used this kit for years, since the bottles were solid white with black caps. This is still the same formula, don't worry. Cheaper than buying from a regular store. I use this once a week. Make sure you use a timer & follow the instructions. If you try to just guess the time, you will end up with a sore face because you'll get distracted by how good it feels on your skin & end up rubbing it around for 3 minutes. I have very dry, sensitive skin so I don't exfoliate a lot. I have a lot of acne scars, and this helps lighten them. It even helps with existing acne.

My only gripe with this product is that I always run out of one before the other. Usually the scrub first. I'm probably using too much though. But you don't really need a lot. To save how much activator you use, rinse the scrub off your hands before that step so you have a little dampness on your hands, and you don't waste activator trying to dissolve the scrub leftover on your fingers. And only use this on a dry face BEFORE a shower. Don't use it after a shower when your skin is still wet & warm or it will hurt. You can use a makeup wipe but only on your eye makeup. This stuff removes face makeup just as well. You don't want any extra moisture on your face.

I am head over heels in love with this stuff. I don't splurge on face care, but this is a must-have. I use a $3 aveeno bar & cheap cerave moisturizer. Oh yeah, and don't use any type of special moisturizer after this. Nothing with acids or charcoal or anything that has a special use like "clearing" or "brightening." Only use a basic gentle moisturizer like cerave. Your skin will be sensitive after, and special face creams could hurt you. After using, dry off your face about 80% of the way so it's slightly damp, then add moisturizer. Your skin will drink it right up and it feels amazing. You will want to sit there for 5 minutes just rubbing it in cause it feels so nice, and your skin will feel so soft you won't wanna keep your hands off it. You might even want to add a 2nd helping of moisturizer. Your makeup will apply so much better, and you won't even need much because this makes your skin bright & fresh looking. If you're an eyebrow-lover, you'll love how easily your pencil or dipbrow glides onto your skin. I actually use this scrub directly on my eyebrows for a few seconds. You're constantly using heavy waxy pomades & pencils on them, and that can cause buildup. This scrub negates that and leaves your brow area super soft.

I recommend this for anyone of any age or gender. I'm 23 and I started using when I was 17 or 18. You will not regret it. It will probably burn the first few times, but you will get used to it. Try only using each step for 40 seconds the first time instead of the whole minute. And remember, use small, gentle circles. It feels so good that sometimes you want to rub harder but it will hurt. The activator part feels weird but you will get used to that too. To use less activator, tilt your head back and squeeze some directly onto your forehead, cheeks, and chin, then start rubbing in.a keep your hands off it. column6: Salon Sundry Spa Paraffin Wax Warmer
column13: Nice product but Be Sure You Have Time to Use It
column14:
Works well and heat feels good on arthritic hands but it doesn't last long even though I wrap my hands in plastic bags and bath towel. I leave it on for about 10 minutes but the feeling of heat subsides in about 5 mins. My hands are less painful overall so it must be helping. I set it up on an old microwave cart that I put in the bathroom. You need space for it and the only problem with the cart is it is too high if I want to dip a foot (one foot at a time would fit). I haven't tried that yet but would only move the unit to the floor before plugging it in as you don't want to spill any hot wax! I generally turn the unit on after lunch. It takes nearly 2 hours to melt 5 lbs of wax. I bought Paramed wax on Amazon. 6 lbs was about $25. It's good and very oily so no need to add mineral oil. I only added 5-6 drops of peppermint oil as recommended by my physical therapist. May try adding more but we do notice a slight odor from it. Not unpleasant, just something we are not used to.

One thing I cannot tell is whether the interior is plastic or metal. My PT said to get metal as some plastic units leak. Inside and out is all white and when you tap on the inside it sounds more like plastic than metal. But it hasn't leaked after the first week. Overall, happy with it. But be aware it does take some dedicated space, and then commitment to use it regularly. It is easier to do one hand at a time unless you have someone to help cover your second hand. It would be hard to do both hands if you're alone. I do one at a time so I have the other hand free to use my iPad, TV remote or whatever.

I believe the product was fulfilled by Amazon, but not sure. In any case, after 5 business days, it had not even been processed for shipping! I contacted Amazon and they expedited it but be aware if you use free shipping, that apparently also means you're at the back of the line for even starting to process your order! Pay for shipping if you're in a hurry. I had the wax within 2 or 3 days and it sat here waiting for the warmer!

As others have noted, the instructions are a joke, written by someone with little knowledge of English. Another reviewer wrote out the directions, which was helpful. Also, go to YouTube and a couple of physical therapists have a very good video on how to use it. You must dip your hands or feet at least 5 times to get enough wax layer to provide enough heat. I sometimes do more dips.

So my advice is to be aware it takes time to melt the wax, and time to use it daily, or whenever. If you don't have the time, this will just be another dust catcher. But if you can invest the time, it does seem to help arthritis pain. My PT said I'd notice more benefit over time as it reduces inflammation each time you use it.in 2 or 3 days and it sat here waiting for the warmer!

column6: Natrapel 8 Hour Insect Repellent 5oz Spray (6 Pack)
column14: This really works, keeps the mosquitoes far away. Very effective. I also bought it for my son who plays pro baseball in the summers, and who has already had Lyme disease once from tick bites. He and his teammates in the bullpen, who also use it, find it to be very effective also.  Just another tip if you use it. Some people have noted that it leaves an oily residue when you spray it on, which I found to be  unpleasantly greasy also. I got around this by not spraying it directly on my skin. Instead I spray it on a folded piece of paper towel and then dab or streak the paper towel on my skin. When the paper towel no longer feels moist I just spray it again, and so on until all exposed skin has been touched. It doesn't go on oily if you do that, but the picardin is so effective that it still works.

column6: PURA D'OR Anti-Hair Loss Shampoo (Gold Label), Effective Solution for Hair Thinning & Breakage, NEW & IMPROVED PUMPS, 16 Fluid Ounce (Packaging May Vary)
column13: a great feeling of smooth, natural wash and softer hair
column14:
I have a hair loss problem on the sides of the forehead, and recently have gotten more worried about increasing amount fallen hair after shampoo. So I decided to invest some more money into a quality anti-hair loss shampoo, and found this to be the most popular in the market.
When I finally applied it onto my wet hair, my first impression was 'nothing feels different' and 'will this really work?' Then as I massaged my scalp with it, very fine foam started to form, and it gave a natural, smooth feeling of scalp cleanse. Throughout the entire washing process, I indeed felt no hint of chemical reactions or artificial feeling of freshness, it just felt like a natural wash in a forest, with the slight scent of herbs and aroma. And when I blow-dried my hair afterwards, it had definitely gotten more volume and each strand seemed coated. I was worried the natural formula would render stiff hair, but to my surprise, my hair as a whole felt much softer afterwards, too. I have only used it once so far, but I have a prettty good feeling this shampoo will guard my hair from loss, if not grow, at this rate.

column14: I did NOT purchase this product from Amazon but have used this product using the "Anthony Dickey Method" (haven't heard of him???) check out youtube or "Hairrules.com" and he has videos on his products and method..I've been natural for a year and a couple of months and i have watch LOTS of youtubers none of their methods worked for ME!  Really never had a successful twist-0ut, braid-out, bantu knot, wash no go etc..Anthony Dickeys method of doing EVERYTHING IN the shower with SOAKING WET HAIR AND USING PRODUCTS GENEROUSLY has provided me with the most beautiful wash n go EVER.....people that complain about the HARD/crunchy hair probably used to much because you don't need much but most styling gels will create this but all you have to do is scrunch your hair either with an oil or just use your fingers.  That HARD feeling is just the cast that a styling product provides, it can be removed easily by scrunching your hair with fingers......this product does produce flaking when I am crunching...but not to the point where I would rate this product less than a 5!  After I remove that CAST of hard hair, I have beautiful SoFT curls.....it took ME - a year and a half of being natural and thousands of dollars later to realize that I have found what works for me!  I have never  seen my curl pattern look like this......I contributed this to the Anthony Dickey method for sure but this product is what I have used with his method....I in love with my with curl pattern now! column6: Majestic Pure Indian Healing Clay Powder, 16 Oz
column14:
EXCELLENT, EXCELLENT AND ESPECIAL QUALITY

Bentonite is one of the most effective and powerful healing clays. It can be used externally as a clay poultice, mud pack or in the bath and, in skin care recipes. This is a good quality Bentonite grey/cream in color, very fine, velveteen feel and is odorless and non-staining because it came from aged volcanic ash. I use it in my skin because bentonite has strong negative charge when hydrated which bonds to the positive charge in many toxins, heavy metals, impurities and chemicals, absorbing them.

How I use it as well you can do:

I apply a past of bentonite clay and water on any skin irritation like blemishes, insect bites, cuts, skin itching, or burns. I leave it on until it dries and wash off after several minutes. This is said to be especially calming to skin itching from eczema, psoriasis, viral rash, active acne, etc.
For smooth and healthy face skin, leave on for 20 minutes and wash off. I typically do this twice a week.
I sometimes add about 1/4 cup of Bentonite Clay to a bath for a relaxing detox bath that softens skin.

A slight redness may appear after removing the clay. This is normal and will disappear in approximately 30minutes.

But which is better, sodium or calcium bentonite?
Sodium bentonite expands when wet, absorbing as much as several times its dry mass in water. So, to remove dirty stuffs this is the best

Calcium bentonite is a useful adsorbent for fats and oils because the main active ingredient of fuller earth, so for oil skin take it for you

Good product, take the chance to improved you skin and health

column6: BEST Dead Sea Mud Facial Mask + FREE BONUS EBOOK - Cleansing Acne & Pore Reducing Anti Aging Mask for Clear, Radiant Skin - 6 oz
column14:
At 25, I have pretty acne prone skin. Partially genetics, partially life choices/diet. I truly feel tat masks really have helped my skin. I had used the mask about three times with positive results. It seemed to "reset" my skin. Moisturizing it and helping to clear it any active, mature break outs.

About a week ago, I had the worst breakout that I can remember. I could attribute it to a couple of things. My skin was red, painful, and irritated. I picked at it to the point of making myself bleed. The other day, I got home from work and applied a thin coat to my severely affected areas. Usually, I leave it on for an hour or so. This time, because my face was so broken out, I left it on while I slept.

When I woke up, the results weren't miraculous, but exponentially better. My face wasn't as red and my bigger pimples started to dry up and shrink. I just applied a thick coat all over my face and it feels better. This really does work (again, no miraculous results for me) and I definitely plan to repurchase.

column6: Moroccanoil Hydrating Styling Cream, 16.9-Ounce Bottle
column14: I wanted to give this a fair try, so I used it several times before writing a review. The first clue was that the package return address was from a media company. The second giveaway: the scent. I adore the scent of the real thing. The scent on this is different. It's not unpleasant - a little like the original, but more like a man's cologne smell. The proof is in the results, though. And my results were just terrible. I have fine, wavy, below shoulder length hair that I blow dry straight. With the original, I use one pump and my hair is smooth and conditioned after blow drying, with a great scent that stays in my hair. After several uses of this, my hair was frizzy and dry each time. No smoothing or conditioning results at all, and the scent disappeared completely after drying. I read all the reviews before I purchased this, and saw that many thought it was a fake. But I was also surprised to find that some reviewers found the legitimate one I purchased a few years ago to be a fake: http://www.amazon.com/MoroccanOil-Hydrating-Styling-10-2-Ounce-Bottle/dp/B002CMLS50/ref=sr_1_1?s=beauty&ie=UTF8&qid=1438450747&sr=1-1&keywords=morrocanoil+styling+cream . I had wonderful results with that one, but decided to give this one a try because the ingredients were the same, and the price was good. Turns out it was, in fact, too good to be true!

PROS:

* None

I've been going through different brands to see what will work, and this is the only one I've had no problems with.
"Aluminum Zirconium Tetrahydrochlorex 19%" - That's the ingredient that's working for me right now.

This is what's in Arid-XX, which used to work for me. I don't know if Arid changed temporarily, or if the inactive ingredients are different, or maybe it only works for a while, then fails. The dispenser on these is way better.

The bigges plus here is that it doesn't have C12-15 Alkyl Benzoate, which causes my skin to itch after a few hours, and for a few days. Also, it doesn't have Zinc Ricinoleate, which causes my underarms to peel. This DOES have Aluminum Zirconium Tetrachlorohydrex at 19%. Anything 15-20% of AZT works well for me.

column13: Can be used for Body Art!
column14: I bought this along with Radha Tea Tree Oil to make henna paste for body art. The henna was very pleasant looking/ smelling and obviously was stored properly to keep it fresh. It did have a date on it (it was the most recent crop, Nov 2014). It was very finely crushed and I had no problem making a nice smooth paste with it. I let my paste mature for about 30 hrs (I did stir it a few times during the maturation, I don't know if that changes things or not, but I was nosy). I let the paste dry on my skin for about 12 hours after I sealed it with lemon juice and sugar. It made a super dark coffee brown stain after it oxidized for a day. If you are looking for BAQ henna, this is the real deal. I made 2 cones using 1/4 cup (20 grams) of henna. One cone would be big enough to do both hands (within reason). A little math means I could make 10 cone out of this little bag for less than 10 bucks! A great deal by any standard. Would buy again.

column6: Buxom Waterproof Smoky Eye Stick Smokin' Pistol
column14:
I will not be using this product at all, ever again. I had very high eyes for this, eyeliner is pretty much my staple for life and I was hoping to get another thick, dark eyeliner that I could reapply during long work days without it getting smudged and faded cause of reuse. First of all, the applicator is very wobbly... I had to hold the applicator at the very end to even get a semblance of a straight line. I struggled with this much longer than I would a typical pencil which irked me to no end. After I applied it and moisturized my face, my eyelids started tingling. I dismissed it and went to work. An hour into my workday, my eyelids were still tingling and I gently tapped one of them and it hurt. I rushed to the bathroom and outwardly, I looked fine. The eyeliner was a bit heavy for 9am, but I'm a retired emo kid. However, my 11am it was so uncomfortable to blink or look around, I finally went in and washed my face completely bare. I waited until lunchtime to reapply the eyeliner, and the burning came back. I don't have particularly dry skin or sensitive skin but I do have small patches of eczema. Regardless of what it was, I won't be using this eyeliner again.

column13: Holy grail product for oily skin
column14: This is one of my holy grail products. I say this because it is effective, super portable, and affordable. I have oily skin in my "T-zone" area, so I tend to look very shiny in photos during a night out. Thankfully, I've found a quick solution to that. Since this pack of oil absorbing sheets is so tiny, I can stash it LITERALLY anywhere. From my purse, to even my bra, this pack of sheets goes unseen! You can just quickly pull these out from the package, and blot your typical areas of oiliness, and the oils will be soaked into the sheet, and your face will appear more matte. You can tell if you're applying the proper amount of pressure when blotting when you see that the area you've been pressing becomes more translucent on the sheet. Since discovering this product, I've never had to suffer from oily photographs of me again haha!

column6: Tom's of Maine Women's Natural Powder Antiperspirant Stick Deodorant
column14:
It's been about 5 years since I've used regular deodorant. My main concerns about deodorants are parabens, aluminum, and strong fragrances.

I replaced deodorant with a crystal body deodorant stick which works for me. This summer I decided to use this Tom's of Maine Deodorant because it is also an antiperspirant. This is something my crystal stick doesn't offer. I solely intend to use it for hot days when I may perspire the most.

Pros:
It does control my perspiration which is what I wanted.
The natural powder fragrance is nice since more fragrances annoy me.

Cons:
Will stain dark clothes with a white residue like most deodorants.
One has to scrub harder to remove the deodorant from the armpit.

Will I use this product again? Yes but only during the hottest months of the year. I plan on returning to my crystal deodorant that still keeps odors away. I don't mind light perspiration since I think it's healthy for the body. I'm glad I tried this product. It's an option.

Who should use this product? Well it depends on your needs and issues with deodorants.

column6: Ultrax Labs Hair Plush | Lush Caffeine Hair Loss Hair Growth Thickening Treatment Formula Serum
column14:
Initial Review - 4 stars
This bottle is pretty small. I've had it for exactly 1 months, and only missed about 4 days of application. In that time Ive used about half the bottle, 3 squirts per day. So I expect this whole bottle to last about 2 months. I shower, towel dry, put underwear on, then apply this. I am receding and thinning on the front, so I apply 1 squirt in the middle, and one on each side. I do have thicker hair where I have it, so it absorbs pretty quickly. I will say applying as much as possible may work faster but you're gonna need to be rich to afford it. Also, applying mostly to the scalp is a joke, you hair will conveniently soak most of it up.

That said, I do still notice the tingling on my head for about 5 minutes. I have noticed that the hair is filling in. The small hairs make the hair appear "thicker" because there is less white and more dark (I have almost black hair). I do honestly believe some of the hair is growing back. I had a couple (like 10) hairs up front and then a patch behind them that was completely bare, and then the rest of my hair. That patch is now filling in with a bunch of hair.

I will be trying another bottle based on my current results, and will continue if result continue. Now that I have seen some results, I am worried about burn out. Like, will it fry my hair if I use this continuously for the rest of my life? I have no basis for that, just a fear.

column13: Great for acne prone and inflammed skin.
column14:
I absolutely love this moisturizer. I have acne-prone, combination skin that leans more towards the dry side. This moisturizer does not leave my skin feeling dry or tight like some other moisturizers that I have used and it does not sit on top of my skin like a greasy mess. It sinks in leaving my skin moisturized and feeling soft and supple. I do feel it aids in the healing of my acne break outs and has helped my post acne inflammation (PAI) heal quicker. My PAI used to last up to several months and now it is taking a few weeks at most for it to disappear.

It has not cured my acne but I really don't think any one thing is the cure. I personally feel my acne is a hormonal issue which needs to be addressed internally.

The price is more than I would normally pay but I have no problem paying for it. I love that it is made of natural ingredients, including healthy probiotics, and that it provides such great results. I definitely plan on buying more when this runs out and I want to try some other moisturizers created by ASDM.

column13: Still evaluating, tamper proof seal is anything but.
column14: After deciding to try phytoceramides I purchased this product because it was one of the most natural (plus I am a vegetarian and so anything with gelatin ingredients was out). It also seemed that rice-derived was better than wheat-derived. After reading other reviews it seems results are not seen quickly and so I purchased several months supply to give it a fair try. Also why I waited for a few months to provide a review. I already use products on my face and so decided the rest of my body (particularly the back of my hands) was the best place to gauge. l have not used any hand cream in the past few months either, to create a more 'controlled test'. I perceive that my skin is feeling less dry and the back of my hands seems less dry also. I believe this product has improved the moisture levels in my skin however I will have a firmer conclusion in another few months. The only negative of this product is the 'tamper-proof' seal, which is not tamper proof at all. Great customer service though.

column6: Silk'n SensEpil Refill Cartridge
column14:
I first want to say that this is such a wonderful company. I'm so glad I purchased my cartridge from them. So here's what happened...
I received my cartridge the other day, opened it and had to try it out immediately. It worked great. A few days later I got myself all geared up to do my treatments on some other areas but I kept getting an error message regarding the color of my skin (which is pasty white). I was frustrated and called the Silk N' company to find out what I could do to fix the issue. I had already tried everything the representative said to do, but still it didn't work. I got on Amazon and contacted the seller of the cartridge Beauty By Choice and set in place a replacement. They immediately put the replacement in the mail and had it delivered in a day or two and I was to return the defective one. So, here's the kicker. While waiting for the replacement, I decided to give the supposed defective one another try, but in the same room I was in when it worked. To make a long story short it worked. I was the one doing something wrong. Now I know I was in too bright of a room and the sensor was picking up my shadow thinking it was dark skin. Although I had tried this the other day, the light was still too bright. I felt like an idiot and immediately contacted Beauty By Choice to let them know what had happened and that I was going to keep the cartridge I thought was defective as well as the replacement. I asked them to first, please forgive me and that it was my mistake, and to please charge me for the replacement. I received the nicest and most generous reply. They were very understanding and said to please keep the replacement as a gift. Who does that anymore? It's so very hard to find good customer service let alone such kindness and generosity.

So, I'm here to tell anyone having problems with their cartridge, try doing your treatments in a not so bright room. Don't give up as I did. Also, know that you're buying your cartridge from a great company with the highest integrity. I couldn't be happier.the highest integrity. I couldn't be happier.

column6: Philips Norelco BeardTrimmer 3500, cordless with adjustable length settings (Model # QT4014/42)
column14:
Cuts hair well, very easy to use, broke after one cleaning.

I ordered this trimmer a month ago and used it successfully for 3 weeks. When it was time to shave again, I decided to rinse out some hair that had become trapped inside. While rinsing under the sink with the trimmer on to help vibrate the hair out, the motor died almost entirely. When switched on, it can still be felt vibrating, but it is almost imperceptible. You can hear it humming more than anything.

I thought this might be a battery issue, so I let it recharge for several hours, sit for a couple of days, everything. Motor is still dead. Not sure how water is able to kill a device that is supposed to be water proof, but make sure to take care cleaning yours.

Unfortunately for me, I decided to clean it for the first time one day after I would have been able to return it. I probably averaged about $5 per shave, which is still cheaper than a barbershop I guess.

column14:
Like so many others, I read a lot of reviews before making this purchase. I've used Norelco rotary shavers for almost 40 years. My last one was the Architec which, unlike it predecessors, did a terrible job on the flat neck hairs and, unlike it predecessors, you could not remove the cutters meaning it was almost impossible to clean well. Running it in a small bowl of alcohol cleaned some of it but. . . .
The Braun gives me the best shave I've ever had. It shaves as smoothly as a blade, at least for me. With a bunch of acne scars, blades just don't work on my face so finding an electric that shaves this well with absolutely no irritation is wonderful. Wish I had made the switch a long time ago. Well worth the money.

column13: I first bought the Brilliant range, which is absolutely amazing
column14:
I went across Aveda at my hairdresser who exclusively uses the Brand. I first bought the Brilliant range, which is absolutely amazing.
But I live in a very dry climate and needed extra moisture. So I ended up getting the Dry Remedy range.

I've read reviews of these products, and people don't give it justice, for the simple reason, I think that they do not know hot to properly use it.

You need a small amount, make it foam in your hands, then apply. After applying, had some water, then massage into the scalp and the length of the hair. Repeat this process once more. Then, use the conditionner. Leave it in for 3-4 minutes and rinse thoroughly. Finally, use the oil. And voilÃ , smooth, silky and tamed hair. This is seriously and amazing products for those in need of extra moisture.

column13: I wanted to love this, because I love TRESemme...
column14:
I have baby-fine, bra-strap-length hair that gets disgustingly greasy 24 hours after a wash. I've been searching for years for a volumizing shampoo that would really work on my hair - particularly one that would provide volume that lasts more than an hour or so after a blow-dry. I read a raving review about how amazing and life-changing this shampoo is, so I figured I'd give it a whirl. Not to mention, I've tried other TRESemme shampoos and LOVED them (the shampoo AND the price tag!) so I had faith that maybe this shampoo would be *the one* that I've been looking for.

Well, it's not.

My hair is probably more flat and limp than it's been in the past ten years. If I blow-dry my hair, it looks great for about 20 minutes, at which point all volume goes away, and my hair is flat against my head again. At this point I'm just desperately trying to get through the rest of this giant bottle so that I can try something else. Maybe it works wonders for some people, but it's just not for me. Sorry, TRESemme, but this one was a miss for me...

column6: Garnier Olia Oil Powered Permanent Hair Color, 7.0 Dark Blonde (Packaging May Vary)
column13: I liked the original application bottle
column14:
A BLOOD BATH IN THE SHOWER!!

After seeing all those fabulous commercials with women with just colored, shiny, silky-smooth hair, I decided to opt in for this new color experience by Garnier. I chose 4.60, the Dark Intense Auburn. Initially, I liked the original application bottle, and I was impressed at how easily the color and the toner came out of their respective tubes. Product LOOKED smooth and smelled good too. I shook the bottle to blend the ingredients as per instructions, and began applying it. Moments later, as I continued, the hair color itself became sticky, and caused my hair to wad up. Now, I'll admit my hair is long, and it IS an effort to distribute color evenly, but what caused my real concern, is that the base of the applicator bottle is rather round, and dome-like. It slipped out of my gloved hands several times and splattered into the sink. That bottle is very hard to hang onto, because of it's shape, especially when your hands are wet with hair color! I ended up having to rinse my gloves to wash the sink clean several times (and surrounding areas as well) That said, it seemed the color was still making my hair tangled and stiff. I used a small hair brush to blend it into my roots and the ends. (More rinsing & cleaning) I then piled all my hair up, clipped it, and went off to play Candy Crush for 30 minutes......
Next: THE SHOWER INCIDENT!!!!!!!!!!1
Let's just say, that I closed my eyes, and started rinsing the gore out of my hair. When I opened my eyes, ==== The whole shower floor, walls, curtain, and my body was SPLATTERED in what looked like something from a horror movie!! OMG...OMG.... I applied the conditioner they so thoughtfully provided, and now I see why they advise you to leave it in for two minutes. YOU NEED THAT TIME TO WASH AWAY THE EVIDENCE OF A MASSACRE!! It was like a bad episode of Criminal Minds without Shemar Moore in the shower with me! Afterwards, I towel-dried my hair, and let it dry naturally. VERY pretty color, the little grey I had (or as I like to say, "My Bling Strands" were gone, and my hair was great. ONE THING: NO shine. At all. Not even a little bit. Le Sigh.......tty color, the little grey I had (or as I like to say, "My Bling Strands" were gone, and my hair was great. ONE THING: NO shine. At all. Not even a little bit. Le Sigh.......

column6: Contouring Slimming Body Wrap All Natural Ingredients Works to Firm Tone Tighten and Reduce Cellulite 15 Applications
column13: Nice for making skin super soft and smooth, although it's not going to be a miracle weight loss cure
column14:
These body wraps by DIP Trade are nice to pamper and treat the skin around my abdomen. Now I should make it clear that these are not some sort of miracle cure to instantly take weight off your body - unfortunately no such thing exists! What they do succeed in doing, however, is making the skin feel soft and supple. The wraps are quite easy to use. Following the instructions, I started by peeling back the middle section and applying it around my navel. I could immediately smell the green tea powder which is one of the ingredients in the wrap - what a pleasant and soothing scent! I then peeled off the ends and continued to press the wrap to my skin. The wrap itself feels quite soft and is comfortable to wear. I ended up even keeping mine on overnight - the adhesive stayed on very well and I got a fine night's sleep. The next morning it was very easy to take off and I could really feel that the skin where the wrap had been was softer and smoother than the skin around it. As for "slimming", I'm not so sure there. There may be a bit of improvement in skin tone, but it's going to take a lot more than an herbal wrap to take off the extra pounds that I have put on since my son was born!

I'm very glad that I was able to order this as a free promotional sample in order to evaluate and provide my honest review.

column6: Avalon Organics Argan Oil Damage Control Conditioner
column13: with painful postulates all over the scalp
column14:
This shampoo did not work for me. I was possibly allergic to Biotin. My entire scalp broke out in an itchy rash, with painful postulates all over the scalp. The entire skin started peeling and it was a painful ordeal. I got the shampoo from my local Whole Foods, and tried it for a month before giving up on this shampoo entirely.

Typically Biotin is known as vitamin B7 or vitamin H. It is water soluble, and helps the body function better. However, side effects of Biotin can be nasty. As soon as I stopped using the shampoo, the entire scalp cleared up with no more itchiness in a week. You should try the shampoo in a small quantity before buying the large batch.

You can review the effects of Biotin more here - http://www.md-health.com/Biotin-Side-Effects.html.

column6: Nanogen Nanofibers Auburn Color
column14:
I like this product. Does not work so well on the front hairline, but if your are thinning up near the crown this works great. I had a big night out with some friends and decided to give this a go. First I did a test trial before I showered and got ready. Now, I hadn't washed my hair in a day or two, and when i put this on it blended in pretty great from what i could tell. I could hardly see any trace of my balding spot.

So then I took a shower, washed my hair, and after my hair was completely dry I did my application. When I tried to blend it in like I had before the shower, a LOT of the fibers came off my hair and it didn't look as good as when I had applied it to my dirty hair. So I sprayed a bit of hairspray on and put some more on, it blended better but still didn't look as good as when I had 'dirtier' hair. It now looked like I was in the very early stages of thinning, instead of having a clearly visible balding spot. Sprayed some more hairspray to try and lock it in and went out for the night.

The next morning I woke up, I didn't notice any of the fibers on my pillow. When I checked myself in the mirror though, my balding spot was showing a lot more than the night before.

So I think next time I think I'll grease my hair up a tiny bit with some lotion or something before applying and see if that helps.

column6: Rosalina Essential Oil 10 ml (1/3 oz). 100% Pure, Undiluted.
column13: A really fantastic oil from an even better company.
column14:
If you are new to essential oils, Rosalina is a must try for relaxation and respiratory issues. It's a lot like lavender in the sense that when diffused it promotes relaxation and sleep but unlike lavender, this oil just smells really fresh while I tend to think lavender, while truly fantastic, can feel a bit stuffy.

I've also used Rosalina a few times when I had colds or when it felt like I might be developing some sort of respiratory issue and it has always seemed to knock it out.

With that said, Plant Therapy is a really high quality essential oil company and they tend to always produce some of the best quality oils around. With that said, Plant Therapy isn't in the business of giving you a lot of low quality oil like a lot of the companies out there. They simply believe quality trumps quantity and they are correct. This Rosalina has a much better scent then a lot of others I have tried and while it might take 7-8 drops of other versions of Rosalina, this version only takes 1-2 drops. So while it might seem like a small bottle, it should last just as long if not longer than a lot of the bigger bottles.

Overall, I'm a big fan of Plant Therapy and their Rosalina is a must buy for the essential oil collector.

I was provided a discounted product for testing and review. With that said, I wouldn't hesitate to recommend this to anyone and it will be my go to for Rosalina for the foreseeable future because its just a grade above the rest I have run across.

column14:
I came on to Anazon to order this again, and thought that it was worth leaving a review, since I've been using it for awhile now.

I love this conditioner! In efforts to find a more natural haircare solution I have tried no poo with baking soda with apple cider vinegar, hair soap shampoo bars, etc. I just missed that shampoo and conditioner experience.

So I checked environmental working group, and found this company to rank very well with them. I bought the shampoo and conditioner and have been using both for over a year now. Honestly, I don't think I've ever used the same hair washing routine for this long.

I have lots of thin, curly hair. As far as haircare goes, it's pretty easy to please, all the aforementioned methods worked just fine. I'm not looking to bring back the 80s, but pairing this with Andalou naturals hairspray gets millennium appropriate volume.

I hope this will be around for a long time - it's got a great ingredient list and it works. A win for me!

column13: love it, and have now bought two of the ...
column14: I bought one about a month ago, love it, and have now bought two of the lighter pink ones for my daughter and two more of these darker pink ones for myself so I won't be without when the first one wears out!  I have been using a complexion brush in the shower every morning for several years now, but it's only since I started using this sponge every evening that my skin has evened out more and visible bumps are fading.  It's far easier to care for and deal with than the description and other reviews make it sound.

column6: Mina Organics Argan Oil Body & Face Moisturizer, 18 Oz.
column13: Ain't Nothing Organic About this lotion...Dangerous to your health
column14: I'm sick and tired of cosmetic companies trying to to fool people into thinking their products are natural and organic with their misleading labels. I bought three bottle of this stuff only to find it isn't any better than a moisturizer you might find at CVS or Walgreens. This product may have naturally derived ingredients like "Argan Oil," but that's only to make up for the fact that it's packed with cosmetic chemicals. It also doesn't state what "fragrance" is? Which is always suspicious because people don't know what they are putting in their bodies. The biggest offender in the ingredients list is Aluminum Starch Octenylsuccinate.  Aluminum Starch Octenylsuccinate is an ingredient used in foundation, skin moisturizers, lipsticks, eye shadows, concealers, sunscreens and facial powders as an anti-caking and viscosity increasing agent, according to the Skin Deep Cosmetic Database. It is a chemical that is toxic to the human nervous system and is a suspected developmental neurotoxin. The aluminum compounds are also suspected respiratory hazards.

column6: PURA DOR Organic Moroccan Argan Oil 100 Percent Pure Cold Pressed and USDA Organic Anti-Aging For Face, Hair, Skin and Nails, 4 Fluid Ounce
column14:
I first heard of Argan Oil after noticing several friends on Instagram (from different parts of the world) raving endlessly about it, and having a soft spot for all things au naturel, I decided to give this a try.

As a point of reference, I have normal to dry skin and previously, my skin-care routine would include the not-so-budget-friendly Repairwear Laser Focus by Clinique, its Dramatically Different Moisturizing lotion, Moisture Surge, Pore Refining Solution, All About Eyes (de-puffing) and Aveeno's range of face-cleansing products. Having received my first bottle of Argan Oil, I decided to stop the Clinique products and used only (one drop of) the Argan before bedtime and pre-makeup routine. In the morning, I wake up with a bright, soft, supple face, and application before makeup gives me the dewey look - not the oily kind, just nice and fresh-looking (and I'd like to reiterate again that I only use one drop from the pump for the entire face - not sure what happens if you put more, maybe, maybe it will make you look oily). My point is, it has the same exact effects as the more costly Clinique products I've been using, in fact, only better, because it is organic, and not synthetically-made, not to mention that the Clinique products did not give me that dewey, healthy glow. I especially appreciate the convenience of having to use only one product for both night cream and daily moisturizer than the list of products I mentioned above. It's really that good that even my non-metrosexual (read: typical guy, with non-elaborate skin-care routine) husband has joined in the bandwagon and noticing significant difference with his skin.

As a minor comment for improvement, it would be nice if Pura d'or can revise the information pamphlet that comes with the packaging for a more professional and convincing look and feel because the written description (in English) that came in mine was hanging, "Pura d'or argan oil aids in building firmer skin, while restor- " - well, some people do read the fine print and benefit from the little details provided :)

Otherwise, all else is really neat about this product. It is also available in the 2oz/100ml option which makes it easier to bring along as a carry-on luggage during air travel. Definitely will repurchase and highly recommend to those who are seeking natural alternatives and support businesses that are mindful to mother Earth i.e. the company uses unbleached recycled paper for the pamphlets and printing ink used was produced from a sustainable process, the fabric pouched included in the packaging made from natural fibers is reusable, disposable, biodegradable etc., just perfect for the environmentally conscientious.estor- " - well, some people do read the fine print and benefit from the little details provided :)
