column14:
The following review is provided by both my wife AND myself. Trust me, at this point in my life I have no further "beauty issues"....It is also a short but sweet review for ME anyway as this is a very limited use device in my opinion. And my wife and I both come at this review from a somewhat unorthodox and different perspective. Scar Tissue. OK, this is for beauty & "rejuvenation". Say what you will but essentially we all will find our own particular use for it. The review below is addressing the common purpose this was designed for but also from the standpoint of use from Cancer survivors....It is too soon to know if any benefit will be gained for THAT purpose but will update as time passes. This was the preface to the review. Now from my wife who has very large scars on her face, forehead up through the upper scalp area. HER "scar tissue" is mostly referring to a physical scar, one you SEE on the skin when looking at it it. This is the predominate area that she address it for her scar tissue. She LOVES use of it all over her remaining facial area from the standpoint it makes her feel so relaxed and pampered. You know, that ICKY Girlie stuff...HER words below:

5 stars
This massager is great, my face feels so soft and relaxed. It requires 2 AA batteries and works fine with rechargeable's. The directions are very easy to follow as to what head to use for each treatment including picture of head to match with directions. It felt wonderful to use and made my skin feel so soft and clean. In particular, I'm working to smooth out scar tissue on my forehead and it seems to be working. Great product and I look forward to each use of it. The brushes are amazingly soft and enjoyable to use.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
MY words below:
5 stars
I have had several HUNDRED staples removed from my throat, my entire spine and in both vertical and horizontal directions. I look very much like many of the jigsaw puzzles reviewed by my fellow reviewer Joseph Dewey reviews (check his review of this very item here as well- he does a GREAT demonstration!) that has gotten my wife hooked on jigsaw puzzles:-) I don't need to be beautiful, too late! But I am trying very much to survive the many surgeries I just completed with more on the horizons if I can regain enough strength to survive those surgeries. At this point, I am too weak after 6 spinal fusions and a Mastectomy in just 5 months (yes I AM male but it happens to us too) and the loss of 60 pounds of muscle....

Now the scar tissue I want to work on is across my entire back and up my entire back. In MY case, not to try to eliminate the physical scar you see, NOTHING will or could ever erase the deep scars I have. But MY scar tissue is one 2 plastic surgeons have even helped remove for me surgically by opening me up and literally grinding them out. If you run your fingers across my back, anywhere over several FEET of visible scars you will feel jagged, reef like material. THAT is my scar tissue (very long story, no point in telling it here). The problem with my scar tissue its it feels like a serrated knife trying to SAW its way OUT of my back through my skin. THIS is what I want to use this item for. I am attempting to break down this tissue to be absorbed within my body for pain relief. Between using assorted pain rubs bought here at Amazon, along with this, I hope to little by little "possibly" break down some of this massive amount of internal scar tissue. Too soon for me to know if I will achieve any measure of success. Time will tell. So for me, the only item on this (by item I mean the attachment) I use is the "Rolling massager: To make better blood circumstances from skin aging" as it is described with poor Chinese translation in the included manual.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

End of MY partof the review. This item for only around $10.00 delivered at the time of my review is so well worth the investment. If it succeeds or not at reducing MY type of internal scar tissue, or my wife's external type scar tissue is really not of huge importance. It is a device that offers ME a degree of hope, it makes my wife feel pampered. An SHE IS BEAUTIFUL so I'd like to see her stay that way. For all that women have to endure in there day to day lives under the best of circumstances, I love to find a product like this that can give them at least a few minutes of 'ME" time. column6: Dove Men+Care Shower Tool, Active Clean 1 ct Pack of 4
column13: Well designed, comfortable to use, & efficient.
column14:
This two-sided bathing implement is really quite useful. One side is the same material as those poofs that are sold everywhere in varying colors and the other is a mild loofah-like surface. Each side has the appearance of the material that inspired it, but is different from the original.

The poof-like side is a bit more solid than the poofs. It holds just as much suds but is more substantial in texture. While not being abrasive it is also less soft. The loofah-like side is less abrasive than an actual loofah but has more substance than the poof-side or a towel.

The single best attribute of the implement is the design. It has a rounded triangle shape that is easy to grip when using either side. It is encased in a soft rubber holder that has multiple drainage holes (especially along the bottom) to ensure that it drains well and prevent the growth of mold from retained humidity, and it has a string that makes it easy to hang to dry between uses.

The one thing I'm not crazy about is the color. The poof side is a blue-gray color that has the look of having been blue at one time and is now old and faded. I guess this is Dove's idea of a macho color but I would have preferred that they went either in the direction of gray or of blue rather than this in-between. How is that for nit picking?

column13: This is the best value sunblock (uses titanium dioxide/zinc oxide rather than chemical ...
column14:
This is the best value sunblock (uses titanium dioxide/zinc oxide rather than chemical sunscreens) I have found. As far as I can tell, the ingredients are generally safe. Advantages to sunblocks such as these:
-Superior for sensitive skin as they aren't absorbed rather stay on the surface and physically reflect the UV away from the skin (most sun products available are chemicals that absorb into the skin and change the UV to heat).
-Stays on much better even when wet (though you should still reapply as directed).
-Begins working immediately since it doesn't need to absorb into the skin first.

Disadvantages:
-Takes longer to apply and more difficult to rub into skin so it's not visible
-More difficult to remove (you may have to use soap and scrub a little)
-If you become wet it may be slightly visible giving you a white/pink appearance
-More expensive than chemical sunscreens
-Applying when you're already wet or sweaty will make you look like a melting white mess

Tips-
-For easier application apply before sweating
-Scrub facial hair with a towel after application to remove white residue
-Lightly "buff" with a towel after application to remove excess and minimize the "white look"
-The Banana Boat Kids, Baby, and standard sunblock have the same active ingredients in the same concentration and the inactive ones are in the same order, suggesting the products are all the same just different packaging/marketing. Buy whichever is cheapest they are all safe for use on babies 6 months or older (younger if advised by a doctor)

column13: Makes you feel like you're in a pine forest!
column14: I started my EO journey a little over 3 months ago. After attending a disappointing presentation by a rep from an mlm company. It spurred me on to do my own research. I came across Plant Therapy (PT) and choose it as my go to company for essential oils. I made this choice because they espouse safe usage (have hired one of the go to people on using EOs safety as a consultant who also developed their "kids safe" line), have trained aromatherapists on staff to answer questions, support a fabulous FB page on safe usage, etc. PT really thinks of the little touches, the bottles have labels on the top with the names of the oils/synergies. Trust me, it really makes it easier to find what you want/need as your collection grows.  Open the bottle and it smells like a Christmas tree--that fresh, clean, sharp smell. There's nothing fake about it. Pine is most commonly known for its ability to help with symptoms caused from an illness. Inhale it to help ease congestion. When properly diluted in a carrier oil, you can apply to affected area to help reduce pain caused from arthritis, joint and muscle pain and rheumatism.  My other thought is to use it in the shower like a vaporizer when you're congested.  You can put a few drops on the shower floor, or make shower discs--a baking soda, cornstarch and water mixture that hardens by baking at a low temperature in silicone mold. You put them in the shower with a few drops of EOs and they add to the steam. Just do a web search to find a recipe. Very easy. Just make sure they dry through, or they'll break.  I received this product at a discount for an honest review because PT is in process of changing all of it's labels. While they do have the child safe line, they are now going to indicate which other individual oils and synergies are child safe. I checked and this oil is child safe.

column6: Cool Mist Humidifier,Oak Leaf 1.3L Multi-Color Room Humidifiers Ultrasonic Essential Oil Diffuser,Large Capacity,7 Color LED Lights,Waterless Auto Shut-Off
column13: A vessel that brings some of your senses into play, but ONLY ONE COLOR LIGHT!
column14:
This vessel is beneficial in many ways: When used with essential oils, the aroma can be wonderful and can soothe your soul, stimulate your mind or sex drive, or bring back memories. A fine mist of certain oils dispersed through the air is healthful and can help keep germs at bay. Certain oils can calm you and other oils can keep insects away. Just the investigation of the vast variety of essential oils can spur you on to a new hobby. Or maybe: This vessel in combination with a few small bottles of oils can be a great gift--bringing a new hobby to someone that needs one.

I love the colorful LEDs found on most vessels like these. So, WHAT A DISAPPOINTMENT to find out that the only color on this vessel is the single periwinkle blue/violet color LED....Seriously? YES! So, no choice of colors. On other vessels, this blue/violet color is a choice, but there are also a rainbow of other colors to choose, too.

NOTE: In one section of the User Manual we are advised to add 1-2 drops of essential oil to the vessel after water has been added. In another section, I see it says "12 drops". May I suggest that you do NOT use 12 drops? More than a few drops, and you will find that if you let the water evaporate in the bottom of the tank, you will have to deal with a very, very sticky residue. Don't use too much oil each time, and definitely wipe it out of the tank while there is still a bit of liquid in the bottom. This vessel has a tank that canNOT be removed and washed separately away from the electronics. It is a fault of most aromatherapy vessels and a situation that one has to deal with. From experience, let me just say that it is fairly easy to clean the tank when it is still got a bit of liquid in it (with the oil sitting on top of the water). It is hard to clean a tank where the oils are glued to the plastic bottom of a tank that you cannot totally immerse in soapy water.

Also the User Manual has the buttons backwards: Single blue/violet color or no color is on the left side of the one oval button. Mist button is on the right; there is a high and low mist.

*I received a sample product from Oak Leaf.s: Single blue/violet color or no color is on the left side of the one oval button. Mist button is on the right; there is a high and low mist.

column6: CRYSTAL BODY DEODORANT Stick Unscented (4.25 fl oz)
column14:
It's been about 5 years since I've used regular deodorant. My main concerns about deodorants are parabens, aluminum, and strong fragrances.

I replaced deodorant with a crystal body deodorant stick which works for me. It's easy to use and goes on clear. Simply wet the crystal under running water for just a tad and roll it under armpit.

Pros:
No fragrance.
Goes on clear.
Really does control odor.
Does not contain parabens or aluminum.
Does not stain clothes.

Cons:
If you have a tendency to perspire heavily, this product won't work for you.
If you have a tendency towards developing strong body odors this product may not work for you.
If you drop the crystal it will separate from the base and you will struggle to use it.
This particular size stick doesn't travel well. I need to find a smaller one for my travels.

Will I use this product again? Yes this will continue to be my product of choice.

Who should use this product? This product works for people who do not perspire heavily and who are seeking alternatives to deodorant.

column6: Organic Clove Bud Essential Oil 100% Pure, Undiluted, Therapeutic Grade.
column13: Clove = healthy mouth, pain reliever, home-scenter
column14:
I am a collector of essential oils to add to my medicine cabinet. :) I really love Plant Therapy because they sell quality oils at prices we all can afford. Currently, I have gotten several oils to help with muscle cramping and I cannot wait to use the organic clove bud. It is nice to know that the oil is pure, since it is organic, and I appreciate that the specific name is also listed on the bottle. I love the strong smell of clove oil, but I some may not. It reminds me of Christmas, and I will also be using it in an essential oil diffuser to scent my home around the holidays. Some essential oils are steam distilled for the best fragrance, and this is one of them. I love that it wasn't distilled with harmful solvents! Clove can also be used for toothaches, and has been known to kill off the 'bad bugs' in the mouth. I will likely also be creating a clove and peppermint mouthwash for a super clean mouth, but not using the generic mouthwashes full of a laundry list of not-so-great ingredients!

column6: Nature's Cure Two-Part Acne Treatment System for Females 60 Tablets and 1 Oz Cream
column13: They made my skin feel like sandpaper. They weren't zits either
column14:
A few months ago I noticed some little skin color bumps on my temples. They were very little and not very visible. But you could feel them. They made my skin feel like sandpaper. They weren't zits either. Upon inspection they were just bumps with nothing in them. So I figured if I left them alone and took care of my skin as usual they'd go away. Nope. They started spreading down my jawline and onto my cheeks. They were still super small and skin colored and you couldn't see them unless the light hit me at the right direction. But I was starting to get really self conscious. The whole lower portion of my face was sooo rough. So I started trying to just take better care of myself. I exercise and eat healthy anyway, but I started upping my game and taking really good care of myself. I added in a few supplements that were recommended, like fish oil. I made sure I was guzzling water. I went makeup free. I made sure not to touch my face. But, after having the bumps for at least four months, my skin erupted in a matter of days to full blown adult acne with deep painful cysts. It was so red and inflamed that a friend was convinced I had fallen and gouged my face on the ground. She wouldn't believe that it was just acne because the day before when she'd seen me it wasn't there. So I started looking for a product to help since just trying to be healthier wasn't cutting it. Since then I've tried LOTS of soaps and masks and scrubs and acid peels and DIY cures. Some things don't work at all. Some things seem like they are working only to stop. This is the first product I've used that is actually getting it under control. After only two days my skin was much less red and inflamed. It still has A LONG way to go to be cured. But it's getting there slowly. I forgot to take this with me when I went to visit family for two days and in those two days my skin erupted again. Never again will I forget this stuff!
The cream does make your skin VERY DRY and flaky. Be very very careful not to get it anywhere that doesn't need it. I accidentally got it a little too low on my jaw line and it took days to get that healthy skin moisturized again. I was surprised at just how dry it made my healthy skin in one application! I also got it too close to my eyes one night because the bumps on my temples are close to that area. Ouch! Be as precise as possible when you're applying. Also I read that most people apply this and let it sit for 15-20 min before applying a moisturizer. I found that applying the moisturizer spread this stuff around to place I didn't want, no matter how long I let it sit and soak in. So I started applying the moisturizer first then the cream. It does help cut down on the drying, plus it doesn't spread it around where you don't want it. It might not be as effective, but for me it's working much better. My skin is still improving when I do moisturizer first (lots of it!) then apply the benzoyl peroxide cream. I still have days where I look like a lizard shedding it's skin (which can look even worse under makeup), but it's much better than angry painful clusters of cysts.
I've had to experiment, but a good face scrub helps the skin shed quicker so it's not quite as flaky. I've been using one from Mario Badescu that doesn't clog my pores or aggravate my sensitive inflamed face. Just be gentle with any scrub! And don't use it too much, no matter how tempting!
I'm not sure if the pills would help without the cream. I haven't tried one without the other. Obviously I can see the difference the cream is making because it is so drying. But I don't know if the pills would work on their own or not. Since I'm having so much luck with them together I don't really want to risk experimenting. But if the cream is too harsh and makes it worse I'd say it's definitely worth trying just the pills! I mean, compare the price of this to a derm visit and it can't hurt to at least try!not to get it anywhere that doesn't need it. column6: QIANSE \Heart of Ocean\" Titanic Jewelry Set Made with Swarovski Crystals - Eternal Classic!"
column13: Substantial weight, well made piece.  The crystals are a gorgeous shade of blue
column14: This is a beautiful costume jewelry set. I received it free in exchange for my honest review.  I would categorize the size as a bold look, but not as large as a statement piece.  The price is affordable (at least it is right now), and the Swarovski crystals are better quality than a comparable set you might buy at the mall.  The blue crystals are cut well, and have a full amount of sparkle.  My bracelet has three blue hearts, and they are all differing shades of blue. The clasp is easy to fasten; the necklace and bracelet have the same style of clasp.  The bracelet measures 8" including the extender, but can be clasped shorter to fit a 6.5" wrist.  The earrings have a 1.25" drop from the top of the fish hook to the bottom; the heart piece alone is right under 3/4".  The backs of all the crystals are encased in metal, which I like because I have seen sets where the crystals are just painted silver on the back.  The necklace is 16" with a 2" extender, making it a full 18". This is a well made set; it's substantial and weighty and the crystals sparkle and shine.  It comes in a standard paper gift box; mine included a free gifted scarf/pocket square.  I actually photographed this set in a bigger box than it came it; the box that it ships in is much too small to display the jewelry nicely.

column14: First things first, I really enjoy my ring, it's very comfortable, I don't even notice it. However, if you do not like scuffs and or worn character on your jewelry then this ring may not be for you. I wear mine at work and it still looks very nice. But it does have visible scuffing on it, I've had it a couple weeks now. Also, something I noticed is that when I do wear my wedding band (tungsten and a deep charcoal color), this little ring has a tarnished appearance that I am not fond of. Alone it is a perfect little ring, but if your wearing it with anything other than white gold, it might not be pleasing to look at, especially for women, However, I do like it very much and would recommend it if you enjoy titanium jewelry. I personally don't mind the scuff appearance because the matte finish looks better with my skin tone than shiny finished pieces and it cleans well with soap and a soft cloth.

column6: FM42 Silver-tone Triple Row Clear Crystal Crossover Cocktail Wide Ring R124 Size 7
column14: I loved this ring so much that I ordered 2 more! One for each of my daughters that once they saw it had to have one too. I have gotten a ton of compliments on it also. I am a mom of 4 so I don't usually have time to take my jewelry of when needing to put my hands in water or cleaner or poo or anything else like that. So with that being said, after wearing for so long without taking it off I'm surprised to say it hasn't rusted, faded or turned my finger colors which is really saying something because usually anything not real, my skin gets a reaction to and turns my skin green underneath wherever I was wearing the jewelry. It's made from a very very durable metal. It's very thick. The stones are beautiful and don't look fake at all. The price for this ring compared to the quality is awesome. The only reason I gave 4 stars instead of 5 is because of the size. There size chart is a little off. I ordered a size 7 and it didn't fit the finger I was sizing it for and had to take a ring I usually wear off to wear this one on there. So while I do highly recommend this product, I would also recommend ordering a size up. Shipping was fast and other than sizing was as described by seller. I think I may actually order a size 8 so I can wear it on the finger I originally was purchasing it for.

column14:
[[VIDEOID:b4e1b0b5dc045d99683db34fabc9db62]]This review is for the EleQueen Women's Silver-tone Cubic Zirconia Simulated Pearl Bridal Necklace Earrings Set Ivory Color.

This delicate and glittery set is perfect for any bride or female heading to the prom in a gorgeous ball gown. The necklace comes with earrings to complete the look.

The necklace features six ivory pearls that have a beautiful glow and luminescence to them. The pearls are accented by cubic zirconias in vine like shapes of shiny silver. It is intricate yet feminine at the same time. It will catch the eye of anyone you are around as the cubics hit the light and cause sparkles of shine to radiate.

The earrings are light and comfortable. They are the perfect length and will look good on any age young to old. The necklace is not over the top... it is high detail but light. The earrings and necklace both have dangle movement to them. The pieces never flip around on your neckline or earlobes, and remain perfect looking all night.

5/5 stars for design, delicateness and sparkle.

If you have any questions please post below and I would be happy to answer! I received a free promotional sample of this item for my honest and unbiased review.

My one year old son loves to yank on necklaces. He is super strong and has broken more than a couple of our items. My husband wants to wear the cross his father gave him but both of us have been going necklace-less for over a year now. When I saw that this necklace I hoped that the titanium aspect would help it stand up to the terrors of a toddler and, boy, has it!

I ordered the 22" necklace and it came super fast. It has a nice lobster clasp and is easy to open and get clasped without any help. The necklaces design is perfect. The silver is not so shiny and sparkly that a man could not wear it. It is quite strong and study. My son is very fascinated by my husband's cross and has been playing with it and pulling on it all day but it has not broken!

I'm so glad I received this item at a free or discounted rate in exchange for my honest and unbiased review. I'm going to get one for me so I can start wearing my pendant again too.

column6: Sterling Silver Oxidized Marcasite and Garnet Colored Glass Textured Teardrop Wire Dangle Earrings
column13: Fun marcasite and sterling earrings, but overpriced
column14:
I love marcasite and sterling jewelry, and was excited to give these a try. I find them a little disappointing, but mostly a lot of fun. Now that I have it in my hands, the marcasites are smaller and stingier than I think they should be, and the silver is too white

Pros:
1. Fun baubles that look a lot like they're presented here.
2. Marcasite and sterling silver, though the red part is glass.
3. Not "too heavy", though definitely heavier than most other earrings I wear.
4. Come in the lovely black with blue accents Amazon Collection box, so they are nice gifts.

Cons:
1. I think the design is a little quirky, and I don't quite get the swirly shapes on the back.
2. I don't know what Amazon does with their sterling silver. It's very white, and sterling naturally has a warmer tone.
3. I wish these were lever backs; I find the hooks and the plastic keepers don't look as nice to my mind. In this case, the wires look sort of cheap next to the rest of the earring, because they are relatively thin wires as compared to the relatively solid earrings.
4. I am confused by the pricing on these; currently $46.25. These should be maybe $25 or $30.

Other:
1. The listing is off, saying 38 marcasite stones in one place and 8 marcasite stones in another. I think there are 23 stones in each earring and 46 total.
2. As with the other Amazon Collection sterling items I've gotten, they are stamped on the back with "PAJ 925" and "China". Googling tells me that PAJ refers to the maker; 925 of course refers to the silver, and China, of course, is the country of manufacture.

I took the picture attached here both to compare with an more "classic" marcasite and to compare to the size of a quarter (and to show the little plastic earring back that comes with each earring). The older earring has had a chance to develop a patina, but I'm not sure the Amazon one ever will. It just seems like the metal is coated or treated somehow, and I wish Amazon were straightforward about what they're doing with their sterling.

I think they're fun earrings, but they are a little disappointing, too.ward about what they're doing with their sterling. I think they're fun earrings, but they are a little disappointing, too.

column6: 3mm White Tungsten Carbide MJ Wedding Band Polished Classic Ring
column13: Very nice wedding rings at a great price, satisfied so far
column14: I bought this version for my wife and the larger 5 mm version for me as our wedding rings. We've had them about a month now, and thus far are very satisfied. They arrived as described simply packaged in just a plastic bag placed in a small cloth pouch. At first, my wife was hesitant to wear the ring often, because she was afraid it would be scratched or nicked. But I explained to her the material was tungsten carbide, which is one of the hardest ring substances out there, and one of the best priced. Thus far, neither of our rings show any sign of wear at all after more than a month of use, which is what I expected and hoped for. They're comfortable to wear, and to me at least, almost have a shiny, light reflecting coloration that looks like stainless steel, which is fine. The coloration of the ring is not dark at all, and in fact, on our fingers, looks much lighter and more shiny/reflective than the photos posted on the Amazon listing.

column13: Pretty, but not very high quality diamonds
column14:
These do have diamonds in them, but it can be a little hard to tell. The diamonds are big enough to be visible but they are completely opaque and cloudy. It's pretty much what I expected from the piece, but you should just not expect to have this shiny, glittering diamonds, because that's not what you typically get if you don't spend hundreds of dollars.

The earrings themselves were pretty. It was a nice design - a nice twist to a hoop. They felt well made and substantial. They are very wearable - I could see wearing them to an office or on a casual day with jeans or you can dress them up and wear them to a fancy event. They look like yellow gold, although it is plated over sterling silver. They weren't too heavy so were comfortable to wear. The closure is easy to do. They were a good size - large enough to be noticed but not too large that they seemed overwhelming. Overall a reasonable choice for someone who wants substantial diamond earrings but doesn't have hundreds and hundreds to spend.

column13: Stainless steel is great for the sensitivity issue
column14:
I have very small and sensitive earlobes, and many earrings do not work for me due to bulk and materiel used. Stainless steel is great for the sensitivity issue, and and the small size is good for my ears not to be overwhelmed by my multiple piercings. The posts are long as noted in other reviews here. I take my earrings out and clean them with jewelry cleaner and then rinse with water every night (only takes a minute and all my earrings always sparkle like new) so this is not an issue for me.

The fun part is wearing these cute earrings is in summer with the thunderstorms all around, and on Thursday, "Thor's day"; which some claim is named after that hammer-wielding God of thunder. The earrings (as well as several other pairs of Sabrina Silver earrings I have ordered), arrived quickly, packaged in a silver (what else lol) box which is suitable for gifting.

I tried as delicately as I could to put it back into shape, and it just made it look worse. So bummed! I wanted to like these sooo much! Waste of my hard earned $$ forsure! I got to wear them once, and they kept falling out. So, I then spent more $ to buy stoppers, that don't go on well bc the earring is just a hair bigger around than the backing hole.

These are very pretty, well made earrings. But, they are very delicate. Not something you would want to leave in and go to bed. Only downside was I had to buy back stoppers since they are not included, and without them they do tend to come out. But, all in all I recommend. column14:
Bought these for my 18 month old daughter. I was skeptical to buy earrings online that I could not see beforehand but gave it a shot. We had tried several previous earrings that claimed to be safe for small children or have "screw backs" and my daughter always got them out. We were constantly losing earrings or backs and scared that she could choke if happened to put one in her moth. These have been a beautiful reprieve. She has ben wearing them for months and no issues. They truly screw on. They are not heavy or large so they do not bother her. They do not irritate her sensitive skin and they look just as beautiful as the day we bought them. She wears them 24/7 including shower/swimming, sleeping, and during activities. Highly recommend especially for parents looking for their toddlers or children with metal allergies.
2016- we just bought our second pair of these earrings for our daughter who just turned 3. We still love these. They are snug in her ears and any other style she removes on her own. They look expensive and she gets lots of compliments and we don't have to worry about losing them.

column6: Sterling Silver Cushion-Cut Created Drop Earrings
column14:
Crazy fantastic.

First thing, pay attention to the measurements. In the photo these look a bit larger than they actually are.

Now then, I have to say that I've been impressed with the Amazon curated jewelry. For the most part it's been well made, interesting, and offered at a compelling price point. These are no exception.

With hanging earrings it's possible for the designer to really show off the gem. As light can freely enter the setting from more than one angle, it also offers a bit of a challenge to show off the gem without overpowering it. I think this setting does a good job of making the sapphire the star. The companion stones are also cut so they catch light, but don't distract from the main gem. It makes for an eye catching piece that is very complimentary.

The clasp seems a bit fragile to me, at least to open and close. Once closed it seems secure and I don't think there's worry about these falling out. That said, the wire does bend rather easily (which is, to be fair, by design) and I think more-than-normal care is needed to make sure these don't get too out of true.

Presentation is typical Amazon - high quality boxes-within-boxes, with matte black accented by royal blue. I do think the box is a bit large for the product, which I think takes away from the impact of the earrings when the box is opened.

So the takeaway - very nice quality setting with a somewhat fragile clasp. If these are for gifting, transferring them to another box isn't a bad idea. But I think they look interesting. A good product!

column6: 6MM Tungsten Men's Plain Dome Polished Wedding Band Ring Size 4-16
column14:
Nice fit, Smooth and comfortable polish on inside. I lost weight and the ring started to fall off so I replaced it with another one just like it.

Two things to be aware of. Tungsten Carbide will shatter before it bends. So if it breaks while you are wearing it, you will get cut up pretty good. I had one shatter when it fell a flight of stairs and hit brick. Shattered in about five pieces.
The other is, if you manage to bend it, the doctor will not be able to cut it off. Their tools are carbide.

The item looks exactly as pictured and has excellent construction. The back is flat and will allow engraving which is one of the reasons I chose this product. It is the size of a quarter, so you do have to limit what gets engraved. However, I liked the design on the front enough to make the trade off.

I believe these are available for every letter of the alphabet. When you order, make sure your item starts with the letter you want to display on the charm.

Examples:
This product displays an "A"
A - Large Solid 925 Sterling Silver with Black Finish Szira Collection Paw and Hearts Monogram Initial A Charm, Pendant, Key Ring, for Dog, Cat or Person

This product displays a "T"
T - Large Solid 925 Sterling Silver with Black Finish Szira Collection Paw and Hearts Monogram Initial A Charm, Pendant, Key Ring, for Dog, Cat or Person

Additionally, check the width and height on the Product Specification. There are 3 different sizes.

If the letter and size combination currently you want are not available, contact the seller Sziro Jewelry Designs. I wanted 4 of these and only 1 was available. Sziro Jewelry Designs responded to my inquiry their next business day.

column6: Sterling Silver Green Amethyst Ring
column14:
I love this ring! It is classy and beautiful on the hand. I was slightly worried about ordering it after reading some of the poor reviews, but they must have just been unfortunate events. The thing to understand is that this is not fine jewelry. This is fashion jewelry which means it shouldn't be held up to the same standards as an engagement or wedding ring would be.

I have had my ring for almost three weeks now and there is NO bending of band and NONE of the stones have fallen out. The center stone is only slightly loose but has not even begun to threaten to fall out. I wear this ring every day to my job as a receptionist as a salon where I am constantly running laundry and snagging it on towels. I am very pleased with how this ring has held up. There are some minor scratches at the bottom of the band, but that is to be expected with sterling silver.

As far as the color of the center stone is concerned, this is not the ring to get if you are expecting a dark green stone. Also, a dark stone is NOT what is pictured. The stone in my ring is a very faint, but beautifully, pale green stone. Wearing green makes the color pop, but wearing it with anything else doesn't cause the ring to clash with your style.

This product would have received five stars if the center stone was perfectly secured in place, but for a fairly inexpensive purchase, this ring is great!

column6: EleQueen Women's Gold-tone Cream Simulated Pearl Long Ball Dangling Double Dangle Earrings Ivory Color
column14:
[[VIDEOID:c401d190cd9ddfb0510b49bab175b30e]]This review is for the EleQueen Women's Gold-tone Cream Simulated Pearl Reversible Double Dangle Earrings Ivory Color.

This set of unique earrings is very delicate and very cute. The earrings came to me in a signature EleQueen powder blue jewelry box with matching pink velvet bag. I am able to store the earrings in the bag, it keeps them tangle free and super shiny.

The luster on the pearls is very luminescent and ivory. They look extremely realistic. The wires are gold color and attach the two pearl balls to each other - but also go through the hole on your earlobe. It is a SUPER thin wire. I would say even thinner than an earring hook but probably about that size.

The most unique part of these earrings are the backings. The backing IS the second pearl ball. The wire goes through the smaller pearl and holds the earring secure to your lobe. It is VERY easy to use. If you decide you don't like that style - EleQueen has included normal gold earring backs so you can switch out the second pearl ball. It also gives a different look from unique to traditional, so it's fun to play around with the two depending on the outfit you are wearing.

5/5 stars for beautiful, uniqueness of design, and materials of gold and pearls.

If you have any questions please post below and I would be happy to answer! I received a free promotional sample of this item for my honest and unbiased review.

I own many pairs of thin walled silicone tunnels and these are the most perfect thin walled tunnels I have owned. I love everything about all of MYSTICMETALS thin walled silicone tunnels: the price, the material, the lightness, and I love the that these thin walled tunnels actually make your hole/tunnel look bigger than it is.

Now I've ordered from MYSTICMETALS a couple of times and I've been very pleased with their customer service, prices, selection, and their shipping is SUPER fast. My order from their site arrived in less than 48 hours from when I placed my order and they're in Ohio and I'm all the way in Hawaii.

I'm not trying to take business away from Amazon but I found it was cheaper to order from MYSTICMETALS website because their shipping is so much cheaper. Here on Amazon they charge $5 but on their own website their shipping is just $2.99. And for my order of 6 tunnels I was charged just ONE shipping fee of $2.99 and not 6 shipping charges.

Anyway, check out my pics of the tunnels I order from MYSTICMETALS website. Hopefully it will give you potential customers a better idea of what the metal double flared tunnels actually look like. In the pics all the pairs are 00g (10mm) and the silver tunnel in the middle of the pics is my old 0g (8mm) just so people can see the difference between 00g and 0g side by side.

P.S. The colors I bought are: silver, black, rainbow, blue, gold, and their thin walled blue silicone tunnels (I already own their black, white, clear, and red thin walled silicone tunnels and I love them all, especially their clear ones.

column13: The \stauros\" design is questionable but not unattractive"
column14: Fair price for a necklace that is a bit more than costume jewelry but not fine jewelry by any stretch. It's nice looking, though I'm not sure about the straight, "post" design. Is it supposed to be a stauros? The little diamonds are, well, very little. But again, at this price point the idea is to provide just a flash of fanciness - not a showstopper. The chain is kinda wimpy, but again it is what it is. The full retail price is kind of a joke, but that's why it's currently 64% discounted. column14:
I own many pairs of metal double flared tunnels and these are the most perfect metal double flared tunnels I have owned. I love everything about all of MYSTICMETALS metal double flared tunnels: the price, the material, the lightness, and I love the perfect width/height of the actual flares (they aren't big/chunky like some of my other tunnels which makes the actual hole/tunnel look smaller than it actually is).

Now I've ordered from MYSTICMETALS a couple of times and I've been very pleased with their customer service, prices, selection, and their shipping is SUPER fast. My order from their site arrived in less than 48 hours from when I placed my order and they're in Ohio and I'm all the way in Hawaii.

I'm not trying to take business away from Amazon but I found it was cheaper to order from MYSTICMETALS website because their shipping is so much cheaper. Here on Amazon they charge $5 but on their own website their shipping is just $2.99. And for my order of 6 tunnels I was charged just ONE shipping fee of $2.99 and not 6 shipping charges.

Anyway, check out my pics of the tunnels I order from MYSTICMETALS website. Hopefully it will give you potential customers a better idea of what the metal double flared tunnels actually look like. In the pics all the pairs are 00g (10mm) and the silver tunnel in the middle of the pics is my old 0g (8mm) just so people can see the difference between 00g and 0g side by side.

column6: 5mm White Tungsten Carbide Polished Classic Wedding Ring
column13: Very nice wedding rings at a great price, satisfied so far
column14: I bought this version and the smaller 3 mm version as wedding rings for myself and my wife. We've had them about a month now, and thus far are very satisfied. They arrived as described simply packaged in just a plastic bag placed in a small cloth pouch. At first, my wife was hesitant to wear the ring often, because she was afraid it would be scratched or nicked. But I explained to her the material was tungsten carbide, which is one of the hardest ring substances out there, and one of the best priced. Thus far, neither of our rings show any sign of wear at all after more than a month of use, which is what I expected and hoped for. They're comfortable to wear, and to me at least, almost have a shiny, light reflecting coloration that looks like stainless steel, which is fine. The coloration of the ring is not dark at all, and in fact, on our fingers, looks much lighter and more shiny/reflective than the photos posted on the Amazon listing.

column6: FHMZ Stainless Steel Couple Rings Designer Screw Head Love Wedding Ring Gold Finish Sizes 6 - 11
column14:
I really like this ring, because it's different. Since this is a stainless steel nail looking type ring that stretched around your finger, it's really cool.

I know that it says its a screw head, but there's no inserts in the head for screwdriver to have gone, so I definitely think it's more of a regular nail, but it is still really unique and I totally love it. I can see around the head of the nail where there's 4 lines, so if that's the part that's supposed to be true, I don't think that it's really enough to call it a screw, but there's nothing wrong with this being called a nail ring. Because it's still really different.

I was really hoping that this ring would not be uncomfortable, and surprisingly it is not! It is definitely not a comfort fit ring, but because of its design, it doesn't have to be a comfort fit because it's not flat on the inside. That part is actually really awesome and I think it's probably more comfortable than a comfort fit because it's shaped circularly the whole way around like your finger is.

The cubic zirconia stones there in the string are very pretty, and I love that they are at the tip of the nail! Or screw. It definitely makes the ring pop a little bit more having the stones on both ends.

This is a very beautiful ring, & I would definitely recommend this to anyone who wanted to be different, and did not want to have a plane and/or boring ring. This is definitely well made, it's beautiful, and it is unisex which gives it its own uniqueness in itself.

I received this product at a discounted rate for an honest review.

column6: QIANSE \Countess\" Necklace Bracelet and Earrings Jewelry Set Made with Swarovski Crystals - Elegant and Mysterious!"
column13: Nice costume statement jewelry set, stones are cut well
column14: I have a lot of jewelry from Qianse, and got this for a gift.  I am going to be giving it to my mother in law for Christmas. It's statement costume jewelry, and definitely more her style than mine.  The crystals are cut well, and are a beautiful deep blue color. The pieces are weighty and substantial.  The necklace itself has six crystal up each side, then metal the rest of the way up.  It measures 18" with a 2" extender, making it 20" total. The pendant has a 1" drop. It's easy to clasp.  The bracelet is 7" with a 1" extender, 8" total.  The post earrings have a 1" drop. I appreciate that the crystals are encased in metal, instead of just being painted silver on the back like some cheaper sets sometimes are.  The set comes in a standard paper gift box that is too small for the set, I actually photographed it in a bigger box.  It included a free small scarf.  This set is not my personal style, but I know for a fact she will be delighted with it.  I received it free in exchange for my honest review.
